're setting sail on a Caribbean cruise. But, as this weary couple is about to discover, skipping Christmas brings enormous consequences - and isn\'t half as easy as they\'d imagined.',9780099481683,'[\'Christmas\']',3.5,81,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=r58lD61nLEAC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(869,'The Firm','[\'John Grisham\']','Prentice Hall','1999','Mitch McDeere, a Harvard Law graduate, becomes suspicious of his Memphis tax firm when mysterious deaths, obsessive office security, and the Chicago mob figure into its operations.',9780582418271,'[\'Fiction\']',3.5,3372,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=0qI5ngEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(870,'The Client','[\'John Grisham\']','Delta','2005','Eleven-year-old Mark Sway accidentally witnesses a murder and becomes the target of relentless prosecutors and the mob, and the only person who can save him is Reggie Love, an attorney barely out of law school. Reprint. 35,000 first printing.',9780385339087,'[\'Fiction\']',3.5,7,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=u61XH0OJ5AUC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(871,'A Painted House','[\'John Grisham\']','Bantam','2004-02-01','Racial tension, a forbidden love affair, and murder are seen through the eyes of a seven-year-old boy in a 1950s Southern cotton-farming community.',9780385337939,'[\'Fiction\']',4,66,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=PKKsy1PSK-UC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(872,'Dragonfly in Amber','[\'Diana Gabaldon\']','Delta','2001-08-01','In eighteenth-century Scotland, Claire Randall and her raven-haired daughter, Brianna, return to the majestic hills where Claire recalls the love of her life--gallant warrior James Fraser.',9780385335973,'[\'Fiction\']',4,2960,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=yYc_PgAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(873,'The Dragon\'s Eye','[\'Dugald Steer\']','Cand