es the making of the movie trilogy based on J.R.R. Tolkien\'s The Lord of the Rings, covering topics including filming locations, special effects, costumes, battle scenes, characters, and music.',9780618260225,'[\'Performing Arts\']',5,1,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=7bT5gO7CrVMC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(1136,'Animals in Translation','[\'Temple Grandin\', \'Catherine Johnson\']','Houghton Mifflin Harcourt','2005','An animal scientist draws on her experience as an autistic to identify commonalities between animals and autistics, offering insight into how animals process sensory information and how they often possess unrecognized talents.',9780156031448,'[\'Nature\']',4,1189,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=1WUg8XnuL-wC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(1137,'God\'s Covenant with Animals','[\'J. R. Hyland\']','Lantern Books','2000','From Genesis to Christ, the Bible testifies to God\'s love and concern for animals. The same self-centeredness that led to the violence and abuse that has marked human relations also caused the abuse and exploitation of animals. The Bible, argues the author, calls upon human beings to stop their violence and abuse of each other and all other creatures. It promises that when they do, the sorrow and the suffering that marks life on Earth will give way to the joy and peace that God ordained at the creation of the world. In these compelling essays, Rev. J. R. Hyland explores the Old and New Testament and reveals the prophetic voices that called for compassion over killing, and humane concern for all of God\'s creation.',9781930051157,'[\'Nature\']',5,1,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=nRMxniy-eKoC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(1138,'Lafayette','[\'Harlow Giles Unger\']','Wiley','2003-11-04','Acclaim for Lafayette I found Mr. Unger\'s book exceptionally well done. It\'s an admirable account of the marquis\'s two revolutions-one might even say his two lives-the French and the American. It also captures the private Lafayette and his remarkable wife, Adrienne, in often moving detail. -Thomas Fleming, author, Liberty!: The American Revolution Harlow Unger\'s Lafayette is a remarkable and dramatic account of a life as fully lived as it is possible to imagine, that of Gilbert de Motier, marquis de Lafayette. To American readers Unger\'s biography will provide a stark reminder of just how near run a thing was our War of Independence and the degree to which our forefathers\' victory hinged on the help of our French allies, marshalled for George Washington by his \'adopted\' son, Lafayette. But even more absorbing and much less well known to the general reader will be Unger\'s account of Lafayette\'s idealistic but naive efforts to plant the fruits of the American democracy he so admired in the unreceptive soil of his homeland. His inspired oratory produced not the constitutional democracy he sought but the bloody Jacobin excesses of the French Revolution.-Larry Collins, coauthor, Is Paris Burning? and O Jerusalem! A lively and entertaining portrait of one of the most important supporting actors in the two revolutions that transformed the modern world.-Susan Dunn, author, Sister Revolutions: French Lightning, American Light Harlow Unger has cornered the market on muses to emerge as America\'s most readable historian. His new biography of the marquis de Lafayette combines a thoroughgoing account of the age of revolution, a probing psychological study of a complex man, and a literary style that goes down like cream. A worthy successor to his splendid biography of Noah Webster.-Florence King, Contributing Editor, National Review Enlightening! The picture of Lafayette\'s life is a window to eighteenth- and nineteenth-century history.-Michel Aubert La Fayette',9780471468851,'[\'Biography & Autobiography\']',4.5,3,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=07MCAAAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(1139,'Berlioz','[\'David Cairns\']','Univ of California Press','2003-10','Covers the life of the French composer, including his struggle to establish himself in Paris and how his work was created.',9780520240582,'[\'Biography & Autobiography\']',5,1,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=EwIskvIA5yQC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(1140,'Naked Lunch','[\'William S. Burroughs\']','HarperCollins UK','2005','The anarchic, phenomenally strong-selling classic from the godfather of the Beats: revitalised with a cool new jacket. WELCOME TO INTERZONE...Say hello to Bradley the Buyer, the best narcotics agent in the business. Attend international playboy A.J.\'s annual party, where the punch is to be treated with extreme caution. Meet Dr \'Fingers\' Schafer, the Lobotomy Kid and his giant centipede, \'The Complete American De-anxietized Man.\' And enter the dark and infernal mind of Bill Lee as he pursues his daily quest for the ultimate merchandise...Provocative, influential, morbidly fascinating, Naked Lunch is an apocalyptic ride through the darker recesses of the human psyche.',9780007204441,'[\'Alienation (Social psychology)\']',3,41,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=1B36S7t4k5AC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(1141,'The Glass Castle','[\'Jeannette Walls\']','Simon and Schuster','2006-01-09','In the tradition of Mary Karr\'s The Liars\' Club and Rick Bragg\'s All Over But the Shouting, Walls has written a stunning and life-affirming memoir about surviving a willfully impoverished, eccentric, and severely misguided family.',9780743247542,'[\'Biography & Autobiography\']',4,546,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=ho_gDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(1142,'Same Sex in the City','[\'Lauren Levin\', \'Lauren Blitzer\']','Gallery Books','2006-06-01','At last, a relationship book for lesbians that tells it like it is . . . The journey from sexual curiosity to finally coming out can be confusing without proper guidance and empowering role models. In Same Sex in the City, Lauren Levin and Lauren Blitzer provide women -- gay, straight, and bi-curious alike -- with firsthand insight into the advantages and challenges of being a lesbian. In prose that is at once honest and uplifting, the Laurens relate their own experiences and those of the women they interview, as well as offer serious advice, titillating anecdotes, and a positive attitude for girls who know they\'re gay -- and for those who are wondering about their sexuality but are not yet sure whether their Prince Charming is really a Cinderella. Part confessional, part informational, Same Sex in the City covers the gamut of lesbian life -- from dating to heartbreak, and from hooking up with straight chicks to raising a family. It\'s the book that millions of women have been searching for -- a relationship guide that will help every woman come to terms with and celebrate her sexuality, whatever it may be.',9781416916321,'[\'Self-Help\']',2.5,4,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=mDlmAAAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(1143,'The Girl at the Lion D\'or','[\'Sebastian Faulks\']','Vintage','1999','The appearance of a pretty but troubled girl at a shabby hotel in 1930s France spells trouble for a married veteran of the Great War. Reprint. 60,000 first printing.',9780375704536,'[\'Fiction\']',3.5,12,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=ESGoAAAAIAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(1144,'Human Traces','[\'Sebastian Faulks\']','Random House','2006','As young boys both Jacques RebiSre and Thomas Midwinter become fascinated with trying to understand the human mind.As psychiatris- ts, their quest takes them from the squalor of the Victorian lunatic asylum to the crowded lecture halls of the renowned Professor Charcot in Paris; from the heights of the Sierra Madre in California to the plains of unexplored Africa. As the concerns of the old century fade and the First World War divides Europe, the two men\'s volatile relationship develops and changes, but is always tempered by one exceptional woman; Thomas\'s sister Sonia.Moving and challenging in equal measure, HUMAN TRACES explores the question of what kind of beings men and women really are.',9780099458265,'[\'Europe\']',3.5,18,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=KTKZiwoIHMUC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(1145,'Founding Brothers','[\'Joseph J. Ellis\']','Vintage','2002','The introduction, discussion questions, suggestions for further reading, and author biography that follow are intended to enhance your reading group\'s discussion of Joseph Ellis\'s Founding Brothers: The Revolutionary Generation . We hope they will enrich your experience of this Pulitzer Prize-winning study of the intertwined lives of the founders of the American republic--John Adams, Aaron Burr, Benjamin Franklin, Alexander Hamilton, Thomas Jefferson, James Madison, and George Washington.',9780375705243,'[\'Biography & Autobiography\']',4,45,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=QW-PDQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(1146,'Suzanne\'s Diary for Nicholas','[\'James Patterson\']','Vision','2003-08-01','Katie Wilkinson has finally found the perfect man - but one day he suddenly disappears, leaving behind only a diary written by a new mother named Suzanne for her baby, Nicholas. In it she intimately reveals the romance between herself and the child\'s father, her hopes for their marriage, and her unparalleled joy in motherhood. As Katie reads on, she realizes that the man she loves is Suzanne\'s husband. Now, filled with terror and hope, Katie must struggle to understand what has happened - and find out if her new love has a prayer of surviving.',9780446611084,'[\'Fiction\']',4,51,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Yqnglffxl1oC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(1147,'Hitler\'s Willing Executioners','[\'Daniel Jonah Goldhagen\']','Abacus Software','1997','Daniel Goldhagen re-visits a question which history has treated as settled, and his research leads him to the inescapble conclusion that none of the answers holds true. That question is: How could the Holocaust happen? His response is an exploration of German society and its ingrained anti-semitism that demands a fundamental revision of our thinking about the years 1933-1945. The author marshals fresh, primary evidence - including extensive testimony from the actual perpetrators - to show that the killers were ordinary Germans who were not compelled to act as they did (they knew they could refuse without retribution) yet they killed willingly and zealously.',9780349107868,'[\'Antisemitism\']',3.5,8,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=L11gQgAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(1148,'Beach Girls','[\'Luanne Rice\']','Bantam','2004','Jack Kilvert returns to Hubbard\'s Point with his daughter, Nell, in the hopes of recapturing old friendships, and is reunited with reclusive artist Stevie Moore, the one-time best friend of his estranged sister, Madeleine.',9780553587241,'[\'Fiction\']',3,16,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Z-uLDQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(1149,'The Beach House','[\'James Patterson\', \'Peter de Jonge\']','Penguin','2003-05-01','When Jack Mullen sets out to unravel the truth about his brother\'s drowning death, he confronts legal interference as he discovers that his brother had been making money catering to the sexual needs of East Hampton\'s wealthiest citizens.',9780446612548,'[\'Fiction\']',3,26,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=HQ9DCAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(1150,'The Blind Side','[\'Michael M. Lewis\']','W. W. Norton & Company','2006','Follows one young man from his impoverished childhood with a crack-addicted mother, through his discovery of the sport of football, to his rise to become one of the most successful, highly-paid players in the NFL.',9780393061239,'[\'Biography & Autobiography\']',4,1082,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=gt4Y92REELMC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(1151,'The Blind Watchmaker','[\'Richard Dawkins\', \'Charles Simonyi Professor of the Public Understanding of Science Richard Dawkins\']','W. W. Norton & Company','1996','Clarifies the seemingly implausible aspects of Darwin\'s theory, drawing on the famous watch comparison argued by William Paley, the eighteenth-century theologian',9780393315707,'[\'Science\']',4,46,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=sPpaZnZMDG0C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(1152,'I Love Everybody, and Other Atrocious Lies','[\'Laurie Notaro\']','Villard Books','2004','A collection of true vignettes traces the author\'s misadventures of her mid-thirties, a period marked by her mother\'s glee over the author\'s midlife, high-protein diets, and the publication of her first book.',9780812969009,'[\'Biography & Autobiography\']',3.5,22,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=kupUDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(1153,'Autobiography of a Fat Bride','[\'Laurie Notaro\']','Villard Books','2003','A selection of autobiographical essays, stories, and anecdotes provides a look at the pitfalls and pains of trying to live a grown-up life, contemplating such topics as children, home improvement, religion, and cosmetic saleswomen.',9780375760921,'[\'Biography & Autobiography\']',3.5,18,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=p8tvDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(1154,'The Idiot Girls\' Action Adventure Club','[\'Laurie Notaro\']','Random House Digital, Inc.','2002','In a hilarious compendium of essays and accounts of her autobiographical misadventures and life experiences, the leader of the Idiot Girls\' Action Adventure Club covers topics ranging from bad boyfriends and jobs to embarrassing doctor visits and high-school reunions. Original. 75,000 first printing.',9780375760914,'[\'Biography & Autobiography\']',3.5,27,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=octvDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(1155,'We Thought You Would be Prettier','[\'Laurie Notaro\']','Villard Books','2005','In a collection of zany, autobiographical anecdotes and tales, the author of I Love Everybody (and Other Atrocious Lies) describes her experiences in a driving school class that resembles a cult recruitment meeting, begging her sister not to get involved with eBay, or yearning to do something about a pet store employee\'s ridiculous hairstyle. Original. 60,000 first printing.',9780812969016,'[\'Biography & Autobiography\']',4,13,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=0MvI9LIriE0C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(1156,'There\'s a (slight) Chance I Might be Going to Hell','[\'Laurie Notaro\']','Villard Books','2007','The first novel from the New York Times bestselling author of The Idiot Girls\' Action-Adventure Club, this is a rollicking tale of small-town peculiarity, dark secrets, and one extraordinary beauty pageant.',9781400065011,'[\'Cities and towns\']',3.5,20,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Or9pkgEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(1157,'The Psychology of Winning','[\'Denis Waitley\']','Berkley','1986','A heavyweight amoung motivational writers.?Charles Paul conn, author of An Uncommon Freedom.',9780425099995,'[\'Psychology\']',5,3,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=_CcCAAAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(1158,'Quimby the Mouse','[\'Chris Ware\']','Random House','2003','Cleverly appropriated old-fashioned animation imagery and advertising styles of the 1920s and 1930s are put to use in Quimby the Mouse at the service of modern vignettes of angst and existentialism. As this cartoon silhouette of a mouse ignominiously suffers at every turn, the spaces between the panels create despair and a Beckett-like rhythm of hope deceived and deferred (but never quite extinguished), buoying Quimby from page to page. Like Ware\'s first book, Jimmy Corrigan, Quimby is saturated with Ware\'s genius, including consistently amazing graphics, insanely perfectionist production values, cut-out-and-assemble paper projects, and the formal complexity of his narratives that have earned him the reputation as one of the most prodigious artists of his generation.',9780224072656,'[\'Graphic novels\']',4,2,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=VWFwvusdf_cC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(1159,'Candide, Or, Optimism','[\'Voltaire\']','Penguin Classics','2005','A classic, satiric novel, by the noted 18th century French author and philosopher chronicles the misadventures of the naïve Candide, who continues to manifest her belief that all is for the best despite the injustice, despair, and suffering she encounters in life. Reprint.',9780143039426,'[\'Fiction\']',5,1,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=qesaAQAAIAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(1160,'Awakening the Buddha Within','[\'Surya Das\', \'Lama Surya Das\']','Harmony','1998','Drawing on three decades of learning from the spiritual masters of Asia, an American lama illuminates the sacred wisdom and practices of Buddhism and shows readers how to integrate them into their lives, relationships, and careers. Reprint. $50,000 ad/promo. Tour.',9780767901574,'[\'Philosophy\']',4,7,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=ANptCDDZHjYC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(1161,'Iran awakening','[\'Shīrīn ʻIbādī\', \'Azadeh Moaveni\']','Random House Inc','2006','The repressiveness of the Iranian regime rings loud as a female judge tells her story of demotion to court clerk, her return to public life as a human rights lawyer, her fight against arrest and assassination attempts, and her eventual embrace by the world when she won the Nobel Peace Prize in 2003. 150,000 first printing.',9781400064700,'[\'Biography & Autobiography\']',4,1,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=5Y6fAAAAMAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(1162,'Awakening Intuition','[\'Mona Lisa Schulz\']','Harmony','1999','Explains how to access intuition through the signals given by one\'s body and feelings in order to attain maximum physical and psychological health',9780609804247,'[\'Health & Fitness\']',4.5,2,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=0vvoTWtkXb8C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(1163,'The Grace Awakening','[\'Charles R. Swindoll\']','W Publishing Group','2006-10-24','Swindoll calls all Christians to wake up and reject living in legalistic, performance-oriented bondage. He urges readers not to miss living a grace-filled life since freedom and joy--not lists, demands, and duties--await all who believe in the Lord Jesus Christ.',9780849911880,'[\'Religion\']',5,13,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=GZ0aPwAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(1164,'Spring\'s Awakening','[\'Frank Wedekind\']','Hal Leonard Corporation','1995','(Applause Books). Spring\'s Awakening is a tragi-comedy of teenage sex. Its fourteen-year-old heroine, Wendla, is killed by abortion pills. The young Moritz, terrorized by the world around him, and especially by his teachers, shoots himself. The ending seems likely to be the suicide of Moritz\'s friend, Melchior, but in a confrontation with a mysterious stranger (the famous Masked Man) he finally manages to shed his illusions and face the consequences.',9781557832450,'[\'Fiction\']',1,1,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=0fuhI9YwsdIC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(1165,'A Portrait of the Artist as a Young Man','[\'James Joyce\']','Penguin','2003','Portrays a young Irish Catholic\'s family experiences, political views, and poetic inspirations.',9780142437346,'[\'Fiction\']',3,267,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=RqI4myx1-nEC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(1166,'Vincent Van Gogh','[\'Jan Greenberg\', \'Sandra Jane Jordan\']','Yearling Books','2003','Profiles the turbulent life of Vincent van Gogh from his birth in the Netherlands, through his attempts to be a clergyman, to his years of painting, and finally, to his death in Auvers-sur-Oise near Paris. An ALA Notable Book. Reprint.',9780440419174,'[\'Juvenile Nonfiction\']',3,4,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=n7kv9-zZtKoC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(1167,'Reading Lolita in Tehran','[\'Azar Nafísi\']','Random House Trade Paperbacks','2004','Describes growing up in the Islamic Republic of Iran and the group of young women who came together at her home in secret every Thursday to read and discuss great books of Western literature, explaining the influence of Lolita, The Great Gatsby, Pride and Prejudice, and other works on their lives and goals. Reprint. 50,000 first printing.',9780812971064,'[\'Biography & Autobiography\']',3.5,137,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=_SzZCwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(1168,'The Annotated Lolita','[\'Владимир Владимирович Набоков\', \'Vladimir Vladimirovich Nabokov\']','Vintage','1991','The textural discussion accompanying this novel examines the thematic and technical elements which make it a literary classic',9780679727293,'[\'Fiction\']',4,251,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=JtyJDQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(1169,'Reading Lolita in Tehran','[\'Azar Nafisi\']','HarperCollins UK','2004','This is the inspirational tale of eight women who defied the confines of life in revolutionary Iran through the joy and power of literature.',9780007178483,'[\'American literature\']',3.5,137,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=wp9C3AlZUfwC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(1170,'The Good Soldier Svejk','[\'Jaroslav Hašek\']','Penguin Classics','2000','This text is the classic novel of the little man fighting officialdom and bureaucracy with the only weapons available to him - passive resistance, subterfuge, native wit and dumb insolence.',9780141184289,'[\'Czechoslovakia\']',5,1,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=lRXvOwAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(1171,'Next','[\'Michael Crichton\']','Harper Collins','2006-11-28','Is a loved one missing some body parts? Are blondes becoming extinct? Is everyone at your dinner table of the same species? Humans and chimpanzees differ in only 400 genes; is that why a chimp fetus resembles a human being? And should that worry us? There\'s a new genetic cure for drug addiction—is it worse than the disease? We live in a time of momentous scientific leaps, a time when it\'s possible to sell our eggs and sperm online for thousands of dollars and to test our spouses for genetic maladies. We live in a time when one fifth of all our genes are owned by someone else, and an unsuspecting person and his family can be pursued cross-country because they happen to have certain valuable genes within their chromosomes . . . Devilishly clever, Next blends fact and fiction into a breathless tale of a new world where nothing is what it seems and a set of new possibilities can open at every turn. Next challenges our sense of reality and notions of morality. Balancing the comic and the bizarre with the genuinely frightening and disturbing, Next shatters our assumptions and reveals shocking new choices where we least expect. The future is closer than you think.',9780060872984,'[\'Fiction\']',4,8,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=ss1hXL1PTYIC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(1172,'Three Complete Novels','[\'Michael Crichton\']','Wings','1993','Three classic scientific suspense novels, Andromeda Strain, The Terminal Man, and The Great Train Robbery, demonstrate what made this master of the potboiling thriller the best-selling success that he is today.',9780517084793,'[\'Fiction\']',4,2,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=d1bGOAAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(1173,'A Case of Need','[\'Michael Crichton\']','Berkley','2003','When a young woman dies mysteriously on an operating table and her physician is accused of murder, a colleague\'s investigation takes him from a deadly sex and drug underworld to the heights of Boston society as he searches for the truth. A first novel. Reissue.',9780451210630,'[\'Fiction\']',4,2,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=nHJPPwAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(1174,'Travels','[\'Michael Crichton\']','Harper Collins','2002-11-05','Often I feel I go to some distant region of the world to be reminded of who I really am. When Michael Crichton -- a Harvard-trained physician, bestselling novelist, and successful movie director -- began to feel isolated in his own life, he decided to widen his horizons. He tracked wild animals in the jungles of Rwanda. He climbed Kilimanjaro and Mayan pyramids. He trekked across a landslide in Pakistan. He swam amid sharks in Tahiti. Fueled by a powerful curiosity and the need to see, feel, and hear firsthand and close-up, Michael Crichton has experienced adventures as compelling as those he created in his books and films. These adventures -- both physical and spiritual -- are recorded here in Travels, Crichton\'s most astonishing and personal work.',9780060509057,'[\'Biography & Autobiography\']',3.5,10,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=bCHpFkcw4LcC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(1175,'The Andromeda Strain','[\'Michael Crichton\']','Harper Collins','2003-10-28','A team of scientists struggles to define and contain a deadly bacteria brought back from outer space by a satellite.',9780060541811,'[\'Fiction\']',3.5,63,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=k6LVNLM_D-8C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(1176,'Congo','[\'Michael Crichton\']','Harper Collins','2003-10-28','Armed with the latest gifts of advanced technology, a California scientist, a ruthless corporation agent, and a mercenary hunter face the dangers of the Congo jungle in search of the diamonds of the lost city of Zinj. Reprint.',9780060541835,'[\'Fiction\']',3,39,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=a22NbDYQZtcC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(1177,'Eaters of the Dead','[\'Michael Crichton\']','Harper Collins','2006-08-29','An ambassador of the tenth-century Caliph of Bagdad is carried off by the Norsemen to endure, for three years, the harshness of their way of life and the creatures that terrorize them.',9780060891565,'[\'Fiction\']',3,38,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=o2yu6uJF2SoC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(1178,'Jurassic Park','[\'Michael Crichton\']','Plaza Y Janes Mexico','2006-04-01','En esta espectacular novela, los dinosaurios vuelven a conquistar la Tierra. En una isla remota, un grupo de hombres y mujeres emprende una carrera contra el tiempo para evitar un desastre mundial provocado por la desmedida ambición de comercializar la ingeniería genética. Pero todos los esfuerzos resultarán vanos cuando el inescrupuloso proyecto quede fuera de control y el mundo a merced de unas bestias monstruosas... Parque Jurásico, la novela más célebre de Michael Crichton y una de las más leídas en los últimos años, fue adaptada al cine por Steven Spielberg en una película que se convirtió en el gran acontecimiento cinematográfico de 1993 y en el origen del fenómeno de masas llamado dinomanía. “Una joya de la fantasía científica.” El País',9780307348135,'[\'Fiction\']',5,2,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=JH5JPgAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','es'),(1179,'The Terminal Man','[\'Michael Crichton\']','Harper Collins','2002-11-05','A team of surgeons perform an operation on a violent paranoid in an attempt to electronically control his behavior.',9780060092573,'[\'Fiction\']',3,16,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=9hERBFsuOcgC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(1180,'Holy the Firm','[\'Annie Dillard\']','Harper Perennial','1988-07-20','In 1975 Annie Dillard took up residence on an island in Puget Sound in a wooded room furnished with one enormous window, one cat, one spider and one person. For the next two years she asked herself questions about time, reality, sacrifice death, and the will of God. In Holy the Firm she writes about a moth consumed in a candle flame, about a seven-year-old girl burned in an airplane accident, about a baptism on a cold beach. But behind the moving curtain of what she calls the hard things -- rock mountain and salt sea, she sees, sometimes far off and sometimes as close by as a veil or air, the power play of holy fire. This is a profound book about the natural world -- both its beauty and its cruelty -- the Pulitzer Prize-winning Dillard knows so well.',9780060915438,'[\'Literary Criticism\']',4,4,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=ps1LlwEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(1181,'Persian Mirrors','[\'Elaine Sciolino\']','Free Press','2005-10-03','The book that revealed Iran to the West, now with a new Afterword. Elaine Sciolino updates Persian Mirrors to include coverage of the 2005 presidential election in Iran. As a correspondent for Newsweek and The New York Times, Sciolino has had more experience covering revolutionary Iran than any other American reporter. She was aboard the airplane that took Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini to Tehran in 1979 and was there for the revolution, the hostage crisis, the Iran-Iraq war, the rise of President Khatami, the riots of 1999, and the crisis over Iran\'s nuclear program. In Persian Mirrors, Sciolino takes us into the public and private spaces of Iran, uncovering an alluring and seductive nation where a great battle is raging -- not for control over territory, but for the soul of its people.',9780743284790,'[\'History\']',4.5,2,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Nop3PwAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(1182,'George Bernard Shaw\'s Plays','[\'Bernard Shaw\']','W W Norton & Company Incorporated','2002','Presents four plays by George Bernard Shaw, incuding Mrs. Warren\'s Profession, Pygmalion, Man and Superman, and Major Barbara, each with an explanatory annotation, and includes information on the author and his work, a chronology, and a selected bibliography.',9780393977530,'[\'Drama\']',2,1,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=FXaFQgAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(1183,'Pygmalion','[\'Bernard Shaw\']','Courier Corporation','1994-10-20','One of George Bernard Shaw\'s best-known plays, Pygmalion was a rousing success on the London and New York stages, an entertaining motion picture and a great hit with its musical version, My Fair Lady. An updated and considerably revised version of the ancient Greek legend of Pygmalion and Galatea, the 20th-century story pokes fun at the antiquated British class system. In Shaw\'s clever adaptation, Professor Henry Higgins, a linguistic expert, takes on a bet that he can transform an awkward cockney flower seller into a refined young lady simply by polishing her manners and changing the way she speaks. In the process of convincing society that his creation is a mysterious royal figure, the Professor also falls in love with his elegant handiwork. The irresistible theme of the emerging butterfly, together with Shaw\'s brilliant dialogue and splendid skills as a playwright, have made Pygmalion one of the most popular comedies in the English language. A staple of college drama courses, it is still widely performed.',9780486282220,'[\'Drama\']',3.5,30,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=bp7MDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(1184,'Plays Pleasant','[\'George Bernard Shaw\']','Penguin','2003-03-27','Presents four plays intended to both amuse and provoke audiences.',9780140437942,'[\'Literary Criticism\']',4,1,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=mKyvvz8i2c8C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(1185,'The Metamorphosis','[\'Peter Kuper\', \'Franz Kafka\', \'Kerstin Hasenpusch\']','Crown Pub','2003','In graphic novel format, reworks Kafka\'s tale of family and alienation featuring traveling saleman Gregor Samsa, who awakens in his family home one morning to find himself turned into a giant bug.',9781400047956,'[\'Comics & Graphic Novels\']',3.5,2,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=IkHhAAAAMAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(1186,'The Metamorphosis','[\'Peter Kuper\']','Broadway Books','2003','In graphic novel format, reworks Kafka\'s tale of family and alienation featuring traveling saleman Gregor Samsa, who awakens in his family home one morning to find himself turned into a giant bug.',9781400052998,'[\'Comics & Graphic Novels\']',2,1,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=ZwNwDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(1187,'The Metamorphosis and Other Stories','[\'Franz Kafka\']','Barnes & Noble Classics','2003','Bringing together some of Kafka\'s finest work, this collection demonstrates the richness and variety of the author\'s artistry.',9781593080297,'[\'Fiction\']',3,4,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=UbXlAhQvKTQC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(1188,'Antigone\'s Claim','[\'Judith Butler\']','Columbia University Press','2002-04-05','Why do smokers claim that the first cigarette of the day is the best? What is the biological basis behind some heavy drinkers\' belief that the hair-of-the-dog method alleviates the effects of a hangover? Why does marijuana seem to affect ones problem-solving capacity? Intoxicating Minds is, in the author\'s words, a grand excavation of drug myth. Neither extolling nor condemning drug use, it is a story of scientific and artistic achievement, war and greed, empires and religions, and lessons for the future. Ciaran Regan looks at each class of drugs, describing the historical evolution of their use, explaining how they work within the brain\'s neurophysiology, and outlining the basic pharmacology of those substances. From a consideration of the effect of stimulants, such as caffeine and nicotine, and the reasons and consequences of their sudden popularity in the seventeenth century, the book moves to a discussion of more modern stimulants, such as cocaine and ecstasy. In addition, Regan explains how we process memory, the nature of thought disorders, and therapies for treating depression and schizophrenia. Regan then considers psychedelic drugs and their perceived mystical properties and traces the history of placebos to ancient civilizations. Finally, Intoxicating Minds considers the physical consequences of our co-evolution with drugs -- how they have altered our very being -- and offers a glimpse of the brave new world of drug therapies.',9780231118958,'[\'Philosophy\']',5,1,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=pKerAgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(1189,'Gulliver\'s Travels','[\'Jonathan Swift\']','Penguin','2003-01-30','The unusual voyages of Englishman Lemuel Gulliver carry him to such strange locales as Lilliput, where the inhabitants are six inches tall; Brobdingnag, a land of giants; an island of sorcerers; and a nation ruled by horses.',9780141439495,'[\'Fiction\']',4,6,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=5CBvDaWGdUAC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(1190,'Gulliver\'s Travels','[\'Martin Woodside\', \'Jonathan Swift\', \'Jamel Akib\']','Sterling Publishing Company, Inc.','2006','An abridged version of the voyages of an eighteenth-century Englishman that carry him to such strange places as Lilliput, where people are six inches tall, and Brobdingnag, a land peopled by giants.',9781402726620,'[\'Juvenile Fiction\']',3.5,95,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=qk8ps8dtZgIC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(1191,'Fear and Loathing in Las Vegas','[\'Hunter S. Thompson\', \'Ralph Steadman\']','HarperCollins UK','2005-01-01','Stylish reissue of a classic first published in the 1970s: Hunter S Thompson\'s ether-fuelled, savage journey to the heart of the American Dream.',9780007204496,'[\'Autobiographical fiction, American\']',3.5,96,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=FQexYp5ckIsC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(1192,'Fear and Loathing','[\'Hunter S. Thompson\']','Grand Central Publishing','2006-10-20','The gonzo political journalist presents his frankly subjective observations on the personalities and political machinations of the 1972 presidential campaign, in a new edition of the classic account of the dark side of American politics. Reprint.',9780446698221,'[\'Biography & Autobiography\']',3.5,28,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=ulIMHAAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(1193,'The Joy Luck Club','[\'Amy Tan\']','Penguin','2006','Encompassing two generations and a rich blend of Chinese and American history, the story of four struggling, strong women also reveals their daughter\'s memories and feelings.',9780143038092,'[\'Fiction\']',4,150,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=2mgnEzzaJrIC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(1194,'Dr. Seuss\'s ABC','[\'Dr. Seuss\']','Random House Books for Young Readers','1996','Pictures illustrate things that begin with each letter of the alphabet, including Aunt Annie\'s alligator and a yawning yellow yak',9780679882817,'[\'Juvenile Fiction\']',4,83,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=W8jLHoBoy6oC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(1195,'Happy Birthday to You!','[\'Dr. Seuss\']','Random House Books for Young Readers','1959','Describes a birthday celebration in Katroo presided over by the Birthday Bird.',9780394800769,'[\'Juvenile Fiction\']',4,46,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=ODBpx6uhp8wC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(1196,'The Cat in the Hat','[\'Dr. Seuss\']','Random House Books for Young Readers','1997','Two children sitting at home on a rainy day are visited by the Cat in the Hat who shows them some tricks and games.',9780679891116,'[\'Juvenile Fiction\']',4,3768,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=WocHzQEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(1197,'The 500 Hats of Bartholomew Cubbins','[\'Dr. Seuss\']','Random House Books for Young Readers','1938','Each time Bartholomew Cubbins attempts to obey the King\'s order to take off his hat, he finds there is another one on his head.',9780394844848,'[\'Juvenile Fiction\']',4,2,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=yYHNyt-XsqIC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(1198,'Oh Say Can You Say?','[\'Dr. Seuss\']','Harpercollins Pub Limited','2004','Tie your tongue in terrible knots as you try to read aloud. Nonsense rhyming story.',9780007175222,'[Children\'s stories]',4,13,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=r4l8AAAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(1199,'The Lorax','[\'Dr. Seuss\']','Random House Books for Young Readers','1998-02-01','The Once-ler describes the consequences of local pollution and business practices that harm the environment.',9780679889106,'[\'Juvenile Fiction\']',4,13,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=V-cyAAAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(1200,'Daisy-head Mayzie','[\'Dr. Seuss\']','Random House Books for Young Readers','1994','Young Mayzie McGrew becomes a worldwide sensation when a daisy grows out of the top of her head, and everyone attempts to get rid of it.',9780679867128,'[\'Juvenile Fiction\']',4,9,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=rC9T3CBVUsgC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(1201,'Dr. Seuss Goes to War','[\'Richard H. Minear\', \'Dr. Seuss\']','New Press, The','2001-09-01','For decades, readers throughout the world have enjoyed the marvelous stories and illustrations of Theodor Seuss Geisel, better known as Dr. Seuss. But few know the work Geisel did as a political cartoonist during World War II, for the New York daily newspaper PM. In these extraordinarily trenchant cartoons, Geisel presents a provocative history of wartime politics (Entertainment Weekly). Dr. Seuss Goes to War features handsome, large-format reproductions of more than two hundred of Geisel’s cartoons, alongside insightful (Booklist) commentary by the historian Richard H. Minear that places them in the context of the national climate they reflect. Pulitzer Prize–winner Art Spiegelman’s introduction places Seuss firmly in the pantheon of the leading political cartoonists of our time.',9781565847040,'[\'History\']',4.5,7,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=2p2qDQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(1202,'Cattus Petasatus','[\'Dr. Seuss\', \'Jennifer Morrish Tunberg\', \'Terence Tunberg\']','Bolchazy Carducci Pub','2000','Two children sitting at home on a rainy day are visited by the Cat in the Hat, who shows them some tricks and games. Includes a Latin-English glossary and a note on the verse form and rhythm.',9780865164710,'[\'Juvenile Fiction\']',4,1,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=dVVbAAAAMAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(1203,'Ten Apples Up on Top!','[\'Dr. Seuss\', \'Theo LeSieg\']','HarperCollins Children\'s Books','2003','A lion, a dog, and a tiger balance apples on their heads.',9780007169979,'[\'American poetry\']',4,22,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=vVEpAAAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(1204,'Legacy of Luna','[\'Julia Hill\']','HarperOne','2001-04-03','On December 18, 1999, Julia Butterfly Hill\'s feet touched the ground for the first time in over two years, as she descended from Luna, a thousandyear-old redwood in Humboldt County, California. Hill had climbed 180 feet up into the tree high on a mountain on December 10, 1997, for what she thought would be a two- to three-week-long tree-sit. The action was intended to stop Pacific Lumber, a division of the Maxxam Corporation, from the environmentally destructive process of clear-cutting the ancient redwood and the trees around it. The area immediately next to Luna had already been stripped and, because, as many believed, nothing was left to hold the soil to the mountain, a huge part of the hill had slid into the town of Stafford, wiping out many homes. Over the course of what turned into an historic civil action, Hill endured El Nino storms, helicopter harassment, a ten-day siege by company security guards, and the tremendous sorrow brought about by an old-growth forest\'s destruction. This story--written while she lived on a tiny platform eighteen stories off the ground--is one that only she can tell. Twenty-five-year-old Julia Butterfly Hill never planned to become what some have called her--the Rosa Parks of the environmental movement. Shenever expected to be honored as one of Good Housekeeping\'s Most Admired Women of 1998 and George magazine\'s 20 Most Interesting Women in Politics, to be featured in People magazine\'s 25 Most Intriguing People of the Year issue, or to receive hundreds of letters weekly from young people around the world. Indeed, when she first climbed into Luna, she had no way of knowing the harrowing weather conditions and the attacks on her and her cause. She had no idea of the loneliness she would face or that her feet wouldn\'t touch ground for more than two years. She couldn\'t predict the pain of being an eyewitness to the attempted destruction of one of the last ancient redwood forests in the world, nor could she anticipate the immeasurable strength she would gain or the life lessons she would learn from Luna. Although her brave vigil and indomitable spirit have made her a heroine in the eyes of many, Julia\'s story is a simple, heartening tale of love, conviction, and the profound courage she has summoned to fight for our earth\'s legacy.',9780062516596,'[\'Biography & Autobiography\']',4,5,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=ROY68aBz0L8C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(1205,'Pale Fire','[\'Vladimir Nabokov\', \'Vladimir Vladimirovich Nabokov\']','Penguin UK','2000','A novel constructed around the last great poem of a fictional American poet, John Shade, and an account of his death. The poem appears in full and the narrative develops through the lengthy, and increasingly eccentric, notes by his posthumous editor.',9780141185262,'[\'Experimental fiction\']',4,52,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=PerKblgwL3wC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(1206,'The Year of Magical Thinking','[\'Joan Didion\']','Vintage','2007','An autobiographical portrait of marriage and motherhood by the acclaimed author details her struggle to come to terms with life and death, illness, sanity, personal upheaval, and grief.',9781400078431,'[\'Biography & Autobiography\']',3.5,3842,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=MOJZ8ihldbAC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(1207,'Seduction and Betrayal','[\'Elizabeth Hardwick\']','New York Review of Books','2001','The novelist and essayist Elizabeth Hardwick is one of contemporary America\'s most brilliant writers, and Seduction and Betrayal, in which she considers the careers of women writers as well as the larger question of the presence of women in literature, is her most passionate and concentrated work of criticism. A gallery of unforgettable portraits--of Virginia Woolf and Zelda Fitzgerald, Dorothy Wordsworth and Jane Carlyle--as well as a provocative reading of such works as Wuthering Heights, Hedda Gabler, and the poems of Sylvia Plath, Seduction and Betrayal is a virtuoso performance, a major writer\'s reckoning with the relations between men and women, women and writing, writing and life.',9780940322783,'[\'Literary Criticism\']',4,1,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=rH6QReDflQIC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(1208,'Another Day in Paradise','[\'Jim Toomey\']','Andrews McMeel Publishing','2001-09-06','Another Day In Paradise marks the latest collection of the popular strip, which takes a satirical, sea-floor look at modern culture through the eyes of Sherman, his sidekick sea turtle Fillmore, and schools of other coral reef critters.',9780740720123,'[\'Humor\']',5,1,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=yaMEEFASNPcC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(1209,'Another Day in Cubicle Paradise','[\'Scott Adams\']','Andrews McMeel Publishing','2002-03','Dilbert and his co-workers--along with Dogbert, Catbert, and the boss--explore the mysteries of corporate America, from unusual personnel decisions and the worst meetings on record to schizoid secretaries and consultants from hell.',9780740721946,'[\'Humor\']',3,1,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=tHCkvtdDcLoC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(1210,'Moby-Dick, Or, The Whale','[\'Herman Melville\']','Penguin Classics','2001','A nineteenth-century tale of life aboard a New England whaling ship whose captain is obsessed with the pursuit of a large white whale.',9780142000083,'[\'Fiction\']',4,26,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=ob8POxXowOkC&printsec=frontco