o the author, an American writer living in Beijing, the narrative follows Polat, a member of a forgotten ethnic minority, who moves to the United States in searchof freedom; William Jefferson Foster, who grew up in an illiterate family and becomes a teacher; Emily,a migrant factory worker in a city without a past; and Chen Mengjia, a scholar of oracle-bone inscriptions, the earliest known writing in East Asia, and a man whosetragic story has been lost since the Cultural Revolution. All are migrants, emigrants, or wanderers who find themselves far from home, their lives dramatically changed by historical forces they are struggling to understand. Peter Hessler excavates the past and puts a remarkable human face on the history he uncovers. In a narrative that gracefully moves between the ancient and the present, the East and the West, Hessler captures the soul of a country that is undergoing a momentous change before our eyes.',9780060826581,'[\'Travel\']',4,16,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=JvmZjIDiOwcC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(1456,'Wild Swans','[\'Jung Chang\']','HarperCollins UK','2004','A new edition of one of the best-selling and best-loved books of recent years, with a new introduction by the author. A tumultuous history of China\'s 20th century, from sword-bearing warlords to Chairman Mao, from the Manchu Empire to the Cultural Revolution.',9780007176151,'[\'China\']',4,61,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=VSk55Qor8SoC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(1457,'Women in Love','[\'D. H. Lawrence\']','Courier Corporation','2003-01-15','Lawrence explores the complex relationship between two couples in a novel set in a small, Midland colliery town.',9780486424583,'[\'Fiction\']',2,20,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=e9swDgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(1458,'Women Who Love Too Much','[\'Robin Norwood\']','Random House','2004','Is having 