9780006496922,'[\'Clergy\']',4,4,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=_bhPYWs6RrYC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(1623,'The Waiting Sands','[\'Susan Howatch\']','Little Brown Uk','2002','Dearest Raye,\' Decima had written...\'I\'m writing to ask if you can possibly come up to Ruthven for a few days. My twenty-first birthday falls next Sunday, and it would be such a relief if you could stay until after the celebration dinner party which Charles is giving for me on Saturday night. Please come, Raye. I may be behaving very stupidly by panicking like this, but I would feel so much less frightened if I knew you were beside me at Ruthven till after midnight on Saturday...\' Dependable Rachel Lord hasn\'t heard from her friend Decima for over two years when out of the blue she is invited to Ruthven, the fairy tale Scottish castle that Decima will inherit on her coming of age. Her arrival is met with relief by Decima who is convinced her husband, Charles, means her harm. Is Decima in her right mind? Or is Rachel being duped by her worldlier friend? As the eve of the 21st birthday celebration approaches, a shocking event leaves Rachel in no doubt.',9780751533118,'[\'Fiction\']',3,1,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=qalsewAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(1624,'The Hollow Man','[\'Dan Simmons\']','Spectra','1993','After the death of his wife, telepath Jeremy Bremen is inundated with all the thoughts and worries of the people he encounters, and he flees across the country to escape',9780553563504,'[\'Fiction\']',4,3,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=N_7bAoVER6AC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(1625,'Hardcase','[\'Dan Simmons\']','Macmillan','2002-08-19','Former private detective Joe Kurtz finds himself in over his head when semi-retired crime boss Don Byron Farino hires him to find the New York mob\'s missing accountant, a man with far too much knowledge of the Family business, but Kurtz soon discovers that someone will do anything to keep him from finding the missing man. By the author of The Crook Factory. Reprint.',9780312980160,'[\'Fiction\']',3,6,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=YlLPo1ghL7IC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(1626,'Summer of Night','[\'Dan Simmons\']','Grand Central Publishing','1992-03-01','In the summer of 1960 in Elm Haven, Illinois, five 12-year-old boys forge the powerful bonds that a lifetime of change will not break. An ancient, sinister evil lurks in the dark, and when a long-silent bell peals in the middle of the deepest night, the people know it marks the beginning of terror. Now Mike, Duane, Dale, Harlen, and Kevin must wage a fraternal war of blood against an arcane abomination.',9780446362665,'[\'Fiction\']',4,21,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=AVfhSa1w474C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(1627,'Carrion Comfort','[\'Dan Simmons\']','Grand Central Pub','1990','Three elderly friends, who possess supernatural powers and who feed off of emotions generated during the murders they orchestrate, meet every year to discuss their game--an ongoing competition of mass murder and vampirism',9780446359207,'[\'Fiction\']',3.5,29,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=37wWp0ENPXgC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(1628,'The Rise of Endymion','[\'Dan Simmons\']','Spectra','1998','As a final genocidal Crusade threatens to enslave humanity forever, Aenea, a new messiah, comes of age and must deliver her startling message to her growing army of disciples, but not before embarking on a mission to discover the very meaning of the universe. Reprint. NYT.',9780553572988,'[\'Fiction\']',4,22,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=b-iUS4OlDLsC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(1629,'Children of the Night','[\'Dan Simmons\']','Grand Central Pub','1993','Does a Romanian infant\'s blood hold the key to a