ter Merriman and Bran, the Welsh boy whose destiny ties him to the Light. Drawn in with them are the three Drew children, who are mortal, but have their own vital part in the story. These six fight fear and death in the darkly brooding Welsh hills, in a quest through time and space that touches the most ancient myths of the British Isles, and that brings Susan Cooper\'s masterful sequence of novels to a satysfying close.',9780689840333,'[\'Juvenile Fiction\']',3.5,26,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=N5E_PgAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(1634,'Trouble is My Business','[\'Raymond Chandler\']','Vintage Crime/Black Lizard','1992','A private detective is hired to break up an unsuitable romance, find a missing dog, solve a murder, search for an ex-con\'s lost girlfriend, ransom a necklace, and investigate a wife\'s mysterious disappearance',9780394757643,'[\'Fiction\']',4,10,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=_ApgAAAAMAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(1635,'The Captain\'s Verses','[\'Pablo Neruda\']','New Directions Publishing','2004','New Directions celebrates the Pablo Neruda Centennial. In celebration of the 100th anniversary of Pablo Neruda\'s birth, New Directions is pleased to announce the reissue of a classic work in a timeless translation by Donald D. Walsh and fully bilingual. The Captain\'s Verses was first published anonymously in 1952, some years before Neruda married Matilde Urrutia - the one with the fire / of an unchained meteor - to whom he had addressed these poems of love, ecstasy, devotion, and fury. Our bilingual edition is seen by many as the most intimate and passionate volume of Neruda\'s love poetry, capturing all the erotic energy of a new love.',9780811215800,'[\'Poetry\']',4.5,10,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=VYLqlA-NA4UC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(1636,'Beloved','[\'Toni Morrison\']','Everyman\'s Library','2006','Sethe, an