r disturbs the precisely choreographed interactions among the five people living in a beautiful house on a Caribbean island--a millionaire candy manufacturer, his wife, and their servants--in a novel that explores the spectrum of emotions underlying the relationships between the races. Reader\'s Guide available. Reprint. 10,000 first printing.',9781400033447,'[\'Fiction\']',3.5,11,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=5xwgAQAAIAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(1646,'The Guns of August','[\'Barbara Wertheim Tuchman\']','Presidio Press','2004','A definitive Pulitzer Prize-winning recreation of the powderkeg that was Europe during the crucial first thirty days of World War I traces the actions of statesmen and patriots alike in Berlin, London, St. Petersburg, and Paris. Reprint.',9780345476098,'[\'History\']',4,1851,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=XWCPDQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(1647,'It Can\'t Happen Here','[\'Sinclair Lewis\']','Berkley','2005','A New England newspaper editor fights to destroy the fascist dictatorship established by President Berzelius Windrip in this classic work by the author of Babbit, Arrowsmith, and Main Street that prophesizes the coming of totalitarianism in the United States. Reprint.',9780451216588,'[\'Fiction\']',3.5,31,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=PjmwAAAAIAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(1648,'Babbitt','[\'Sinclair Lewis\']','Courier Corporation','2003-09-22','Describes the life of an aggressive, prosperous realtor, reflecting an image of middle-class America.',9780486431673,'[\'Fiction\']',3.5,44,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=7UgzlommGdoC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(1649,'Main Street','[\'Sinclair Lewis\']','Sterling Publishing Company','2003','Features the story of a college graduate from St. Paul who leaves to marry a doctor in a small, middle-class town, only to find her