el as a way back from failure, his wife sees it as a chance to preserve their family, and their five-year-old son sees the evil waiting just for them, as they journey into a world in which old horrors come to life to destroy the living. Reprint.',9780743437493,'[\'Fiction\']',4,2657,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=vUZoxITGufkC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(1864,'The Shining','[\'Stephen King\']','Turtleback Books','2002-10','Jack Torrance sees his stint as winter caretaker of a Colorado hotel as a way back from failure, his wife sees it as a chance to preserve their family, and their five-year-old son sees the evil waiting just for them.',9781417618255,'[\'Fiction\']',4,217,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=QIlGPgAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(1865,'Wuthering Heights','[\'Emily Bronte\', \'Emily Brontë\']','Univ. Press of Mississippi','2004','No Marketing Blurb',9780451529251,'[\'Fiction\']',3.5,7,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=FW9-yWeWuPwC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(1866,'The Moon is Down','[\'John Steinbeck\']','Penguin UK','2000-11-30','Originally published at the zenith of Nazi Germany\'s power, Steinbeck\'s fable THE MOON IS DOWN explores the effects of invasion on both the conquered and the conquerors. Occupied by enemy troops, a small, peaceable town comes face-to-face with evil imposed from the outside and betrayal from within the close-knit community. As he delves into the motivations and emotions of the enemy, Steinbeck uncovers profound and often unsettling truths both about war and human nature.',9780141185538,'[\'Fiction\']',4,42,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=OnckAoxNDV0C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(1867,'Ride the Moon Down','[\'Terry C. Johnston\']','Bantam','1999-07','The popular hero of Crack in the Sky, fur trapper and mountain man Titus Scratch Bass fights against the end of his way of