on','2005-01-05','An updated tenth anniversary edition of the best-selling guide explains how anyone can use mindfulness--the Buddhist art of living each moment fully as it happens--to reduce anxiety, achieve inner peace, find fulfillment, and enrich one\'s life, accompanied by a series of anecdotes, instructions, and meditations. Reprint. 100,000 first printing.',9781401307783,'[\'Religion\']',3.5,10,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=dQ4RAQAAIAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(2096,'Grammar Snobs are Great Big Meanies','[\'June Casagrande\']','Penguin Group USA','2006','A hilarious compilation of witty anecdotes and trenchant essays on the mysteries of grammar and punctuation takes a poke at self-appointed language experts as it discusses such topics as predicate nominatives, colons and semicolons, quotation marks, prepositions, hyphens, and more. Original.',9780143036838,'[\'Humor\']',3.5,12,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=LyoZtAEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(2097,'Death of a Snob','[\'M. C. Beaton\']','Transworld Pub','1996','When Police Constable Hamish Macbeth is offered a holiday at Jane Wetherby\'s Happy Wanderer health farm on the Isle of Eileencraig, he accepts. Unfortunately it is not the holiday he hoped for. When one of the guests, stuck-up Morag, is found dead, Hamish must solve the death of a snob.',9780553409680,'[\'Fiction\']',3.5,10,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=fIUfAAAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(2098,'Beauty is the Beast','[\'Tomo Matsumoto\']','VIZ Media LLC','2006-08-01','When bubbly eleventh-grader Eimi Yamashita finds out that her parents are relocating for work, she decides to strike out on her own and move into a dormitory for girls. Little does Eimi suspect the exciting romantic adventures that await her there! As winter sets in at the dforms and the boys hog all the electricity, Shimonuki continues his quest to win Eimi\'