oks.google.com/books/content?id=2GZlm91NNEgC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(2253,'Complete Maus','[\'Art Spiegelman\']','Penguin Books Limited','2003-01-01','Combined here are Maus I: A Survivor\'s Tale and Maus II - the complete story of Vladek Spiegelman and his wife, living and surviving in Hitler\'s Europe. By addressing the Holocaust through cartoons the author captures the everyday reality of fear and the sensation of survival.',9780141014081,'[\'Children of Holocaust survivors\']',4.5,3579,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=rBj-nQEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(2254,'Radical Chic and Mau-Mauing the Flak Catchers','[\'Tom Wolfe\']','Bantam','1999','Two hilarious essays by the author of The Right Stuff show the white liberal establishment confronting the new subculture, with humorous and unexpected results. Reprint.',9780553380620,'[\'Social Science\']',3,6,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=EJQrAQAAIAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(2255,'Sorcery Rising','[\'Jude Fisher\']','Daw Books','2003-07','A talented knife-maker with a natural affinity with the elements of the earth, Katla Aransen, the beautiful and rebellious daughter of an Eyran merchant, finds herself targeted by Istrian fanatics after she accidentally commits sacrilege and by Saro Katla, a blade-forger; and Saro, the second son of an Istrian nobleman--are forever changed.',9780756401108,'[\'Fiction\']',2.5,2,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=VFgWzQEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(2256,'The Two Towers','[\'John Ronald Reuel Tolkien\']','Mariner Books','2003','After losing Gandalf and being divided from their other companions during an Orc attack, Frodo and Sam continue towards Mordor, Land of the Enemy, to destroy the Ring, accompanied only by a mysterious figure that follows them.',9780618346264,'[\'Fiction\']',4,1219,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=lC_E8Hz-8rIC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(2257,'Death\'s Acre','[\'Bill Bass\', \'William M. Bass\', \'Jon Jefferson\']','Penguin','2004-09-01','A leading forensic anthropologist traces his sometimes grisly work at his Tennessee body farm lab and cites his contributions to the investigations of several murder cases as well as his theories about such famous cases as the Lindbergh kidnapping and the mystery of the headless corpse. Reprint.',9780425198322,'[\'True Crime\']',4,20,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=MTLS-F-HmoQC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(2258,'The Magical Worlds of the Lord of the Rings','[\'David Colbert\']','Penguin','2002','Offers information about Tolkien\'s realm of Middle-Earth and its inhabitants, including details on characters, mythology, origins, and cultures.',9780425187715,'[\'Fiction\']',4,3,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=YLeKUmRahP4C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(2259,'A Gateway to Sindarin','[\'David Salo\']','University of Utah Press','2004','A serious linguistic analysis of Tolkien\'s Sindarin language. Includes the grammar, morphology, and history of the language.',9780874808001,'[\'Language Arts & Disciplines\']',5,2,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=4dsSn0QAmi0C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(2260,'Corpse','[\'Jessica Snyder Sachs\']','Da Capo Press','2002','Provides an intriguing look at the role of forensic ecology--the study of plants, insects, chemicals, and other factors--found near a body in helping forensic pathologists determine a time of death. Reprint. 15,000 first printing.',9780738207711,'[\'Law\']',4,7,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=ahbJG2gthDMC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(2261,'The Main Corpse','[\'Diane Mott Davidson\']','Bantam','1997','Caterer Goldy B. Schulz agrees to cook for her best friend\'s gala at the site of an exhausted mine, an event that quickly boils over with trouble',9780553574630,'[\'Fiction\']',3,8,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=0MGYUfvdKXIC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(2262,'Exquisite Corpse','[\'Poppy Z. Brite\']','Touchstone','1997-08-20','From the author of Lost Souls, Drawing Blood, and Wormwood comes a thrilling and chilling novel that bestselling author Peter Straub says serves as a “guidebook to hell.” To serial slayer Andrew Compton, murder is an art, the most intimate art. After feigning his own death to escape from prison, Compton makes his way to the United States with the sole ambition of bringing his “art” to new heights. Tortured by his own perverse desires, and drawn to possess and destroy young boys, Compton inadvertently joins forces with Jay Byrne, a dissolute playboy who has pushed his “art” to limits even Compton hadn’t previously imagined. Together, Compton and Byrne set their sights on an exquisite young Vietnamese-American runaway, Tran, whom they deem to be the perfect victim. Swiftly moving from the grimy streets of London’s Piccadilly Circus to the decadence of the New Orleans French Quarter, Poppy Z. Brite dissects the landscape of torture and invites us into the mind of a killer. Exquisite Corpse confirms Brite as a writer who defies categorization. It is a novel for those who dare trespass where the sacred and profane become one.',9780684836270,'[\'Fiction\']',3.5,27,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=BuCUSRSuiF4C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(2263,'The Fellowship of the Ring','[\'John Ronald Reuel Tolkien\']','Mariner Books','2004','After discovering the true nature of the One Ring, Bilbo Baggins entrusts it to the care of his young cousin, Frodo, who is charged with bringing about its destruction and thus foiling the plans of the Dark Lord.',9780618574940,'[\'Fiction\']',4.5,22,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=l0hMjgEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(2264,'Bored of the Rings','[\'Henry Beard\', \'Harvard Lampoon\', \'Douglas C. Kenney\']','New Amer Library','1993','Two authors from The Harvard Lampoon present a hilarious parody of J. R. R. Tolkien\'s epic fantasy, The Lord of the Rings. Reprint.',9780451452610,'[\'Fiction\']',3,22,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=9kt9QgAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(2265,'The Return of the Shadow','[\'John Ronald Reuel Tolkien\', \'Christopher Tolkien\']','Houghton Mifflin Harcourt','2000','In this sixth volume of The History of Middle-earth the story reaches The Lord of the Rings. In The Return of the Shadow (an abandoned title for the first volume) Christopher Tolkien describes, with full citation of the earliest notes, outline plans, and narrative drafts, the intricate evolution of The Fellowship of the Ring and the gradual emergence of the conceptions that transformed what J.R.R. Tolkien for long believed would be a far shorter book, \'a sequel to The Hobbit\'. The enlargement of Bilbo\'s \'magic ring\' into the supremely potent and dangerous Ruling Ring of the Dark Lord is traced and the precise moment is seen when, in an astonishing and unforeseen leap in the earliest narrative, a Black Rider first rode into the Shire, his significance still unknown. The character of the hobbit called Trotter (afterwards Strider or Aragorn) is developed while his indentity remains an absolute puzzle, and the suspicion only very slowly becomes certainty that he must after all be a Man. The hobbits, Frodo\'s companions, undergo intricate permutations of name and personality, and other major figures appear in strange modes: a sinister Treebeard, in league with the Enemy, a ferocious and malevolent Farmer Maggot. The story in this book ends at the point where J.R.R. Tolkien halted in the story for a long time, as the Company of the Ring, still lacking Legolas and Gimli, stood before the tomb of Balin in the Mines of Moria. The Return of the Shadow is illustrated with reproductions of the first maps and notable pages from the earliest manuscripts.',9780618083572,'[\'Fiction\']',4.5,8,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=CzXSh4NhOy4C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(2266,'The Ice Storm','[\'Rick Moody\']','Back Bay Books','2002-04-10','The year is 1973. As a freak winter storm bears down on an exclusive, affluent suburb in Connecticut, cark skid out of control, men and women swap partners, and their children experiment with sex, drugs, and even suicide. Here two families, the Hoods and the Williamses, com face-to-face with the seething emotions behind the well-clipped lawns of their lives-in a novel widely hailed as a funny, acerbic, and moving hymn to a dazed and confused era of American life.',9780316706001,'[\'Fiction\']',3.5,7,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=8I-oYgEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(2267,'The Black Veil','[\'Rick Moody\']','Little Brown & Company','2002','The author weaves together past and present and family legend as he shares his personal story of dealing with depression, and his search through his family\'s paternal lines to find clues to his melancholy.',9780316578998,'[\'Family & Relationships\']',4,3,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=AQC2QgAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(2268,'The Twenty-seventh City','[\'Jonathan Franzen\']','HarperCollins UK','2003','Dying St. Louis is turned inside-out by the appointment of a charismatic young woman from Bombay as police chief, an act which launches the city\'s prominent citizens into political conspiracy. Franzen\'s first novel is already a classic of contemporary fiction.',9781841157481,'[\'Detective and mystery stories\']',3,4,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=n9-haBVXbDoC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(2269,'Pet Peeve','[\'Piers Anthony\']','Macmillan','2006-10-03','Unlikely Goblin hero Goody is instructed by the Good Magician Humfrey to find a suitable home for a foul-tempered bird, a quest that inadvertently triggers an invasion by an army of seemingly indestructible killer robots and forces Goody to enlist the aid of a host of supernatural denizens. Reprint.',9780765343116,'[\'Fiction\']',5,1,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=LQxvpqXWS3oC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(2270,'Up In a Heaval','[\'Piers Anthony\']','Macmillan','2003-10-19','When the Demon Jupiter is provoked into hurling his dreaded Red Spot at the magical land of Xanth, it falls to Umlaut, a young man with a mysterious past and unknown future, and his companions to defend the enchanted realm from certain catastrophe, in the twenty-sixth novel in the popular Xanth series. Reprint.',9780812574999,'[\'Fiction\']',4,2,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=irEKXAf229sC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(2271,'Roc and a Hard Place','[\'Piers Anthony\']','Macmillan','1996-10-15','In the land of Xanth, Roxanne Roc, a bird, must stand trial before Demoness Metria and Magician Humfrey',9780812534863,'[\'Fiction\']',4,1,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=8eKZvEWEY98C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(2272,'Swell Foop','[\'Piers Anthony\']','Macmillan','2002-10-13','In the twenty-fifth novel in the popular Xanth fantasies, six courageous adventurers--Cynthia Centaur, her mate Che, Breanna of the Black Wave and her human fiancT Justin Tree, Sim the immortal bird, and Jaylin, a human girl from Hawaii--embark on a dangerous quest to find the mystical Swell Foop, the only weapon that can prevail against a powerful Demon. Reprint.',9780812574746,'[\'Fiction\']',4,4,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=p899yqJFhvQC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(2273,'Yon Ill Wind','[\'Piers Anthony\']','Macmillan','1997-10-15','When a tempestuous hurr