.google.com/books/content?id=d7IcpYWCBFwC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(2437,'Your Oasis on Flame Lake','[\'Lorna Landvik\']','Ballantine Books','1998','In the sleepy town of White Falls, Minnesota, Cadillac salesman Dick Lindstrom realizes his dream when he opens Your Oasis on Flame Lake, a tiny cabaret club in his tastefully furnished basement',9780449002988,'[\'Fiction\']',3.5,6,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=75ZUoDVs6XUC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(2438,'Patty Jane\'s House of Curl','[\'Lorna Landvik\']','Ivy Books','1999-06-28','A whimsical novel with strong but emotive female characters in the tradition of Fried Green Tomatoes features a pair of sisters in Minnesota, including an abandoned mother, who open a cozy beauty salon. Reprint.',9780804114608,'[\'Fiction\']',3.5,15,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=dfpS111TOHcC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(2439,'The Phantom Tollbooth','[\'Norton Juster\']','Random House Books for Young Readers','2000-05-09','For Milo, everything\'s a bore. When a tollbooth mysteriously appears in his room, he drives through only because he\'s got nothing better to do. But on the other side, things seem different. Milo visits the island of Conclusions (you get there by jumping), learns about time from a tick watchdog named Tock, and even embarks on a quest to rescue Rhyme and Reason! Somewhere along the way, Milo realizes something astonishing. Life is far from dull. In fact, it\'s exciting beyond his wildest dreams!',9780375806704,'[\'Fantasy fiction\']',4.5,231,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=BZ2pPwAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(2440,'The Sixth Book of Lost Swords','[\'Fred Saberhagen\']','Macmillan','1991-06-15','When the long-lost Mindsword--which gives mindless devotion to the one who wields it--falls into the hands of Prince Murat, Kristen, the beautiful wife of