ver&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(2760,'A Room of One\'s Own','[\'Virginia Woolf\', \'Susan Gubar\']','Houghton Mifflin Harcourt','2005','Describes the domestic obligations, social limitations, and economic factors that impede literary creativity in women, in the story of William Shakespeare\'s talented sister, who, because of the mores of her time, never expresses her genius until she dies by her own hand. Reprint.',9780156030410,'[\'Fiction\']',4,59,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=dh9gvgAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(2761,'Virginia Woolf','[\'Hermione Lee\']','Vintage','1999','Traces the life of the British novelist and discusses her major works',9780375701368,'[\'Biography & Autobiography\']',5,4,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=ZW4KVeQM6CoC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(2762,'The Years','[\'Virginia Woolf\']','Penguin UK','2002-02-28','The story of the Pargiter family - their intimacies and estrangements, anxieties and triumphs - mapped out amongst the bustling rhythms of London\'s streets during the first decade of the 20th century. The Pargiter children must learn to find their footing in a world of rapidly changing rules.',9780141185323,'[\'Fiction\']',3.5,8,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=26uGvwEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(2763,'Three Guineas','[\'Virginia Woolf\', \'Jane Marcus\', \'Mark Hussey\']','Houghton Mifflin Harcourt','2006','The gifted English writer submits a strong plea for intellectual freedom, women\'s rights, and the cessation of war, in an annotated series of letters. Reprint. 12,000 first printing.',9780156031639,'[\'Fiction\']',3.5,5,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=MVdivgAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(2764,'The Little Red Lighthouse and the Great Gray Bridge','[\'Hildegarde Hoyt Swift\', \'Lynd Ward\']','Houghton Mifflin Harcourt','2003-04-01','A little lighthouse on the Hud