ity and alignment.',9780787976385,'[\'Business & Economics\']',3.5,5,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=P17HAgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(2805,'Moral Politics','[\'George Lakoff\']','University of Chicago Press','2002-05','In this classic text, Lakoff analyses the unconscious and rhetorical worldviews of liberals and conservatives, discovering radically different but remarkably consistent conceptions of morality.',9780226467719,'[\'Language Arts & Disciplines\']',4,3,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=R-4YBCYx6YsC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(2806,'The Divine Comedy: Inferno','[\'Dante Alighieri\']','Penguin Classics','1984','This translation of Dante\'s Inferno aims to preserve Dante\'s natural style while capturing the movement of the original Italian verse. The blank verse rendition of the poet\'s journey through the circles of hell re-creates for the modern reader the meanings Dante\'s poem had for contemporaries.',9780140444414,'[\'Christianity\']',4,2,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=96pWAAAAYAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(2807,'The Divine Comedy - Hell','[\'Dante Alighieri\']','Penguin','1950-06-01','A verse translation, with critical commentaries, of the thirty-three cantos of Dante\'s allegorical poem',9780140440065,'[\'Poetry\']',3.5,27,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=JvarpYw_jWwC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(2808,'Inferno','[\'Dante Alighieri\']','Bantam Classics','1982','An informative introduction and commentary accompany this classic translation of Dante\'s epic poem about a spiritual pilgrim being led by Virgil through the nine circles of hell, available in a dual-language edition. Reissue.',9780553213393,'[\'Fiction\']',5,1,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=g_dvDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(2809,'Purgatorio','[\'Dante Al