bout Will Navidson\'s house, the more frightened he becomes. Paranoia besets him. The worst part is that he can\'t just dismiss the notebook as the ramblings of a crazy old man. He\'s starting to notice things changing around him . . . Immensely imaginative. Impossible to put down. Impossible to forget. House of Leavesis thrilling, terrifying and unlike anything you have ever read before.',9780385603102,'[\'Experimental fiction\']',3.5,3120,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=-ndjtDlVIKsC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(3401,'A Parchment of Leaves','[\'Silas House\']','Ballantine Reader\'s Circle','2003','In 1917, a Cherokee woman who leaves her community to marry a white man finds herself isolated and discriminated against as she tries to settle in to her new life. By the author of Clay\'s Quilt. Reprint.',9780345464972,'[\'Fiction\']',4,8,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=haqGzhEEv9QC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(3402,'The Areas of My Expertise','[\'John Hodgman\']','Riverhead Books','2006','A humorous compendium of reference tables, trivia, and wisdom--largely invented by the author--lists the mottoes of the fifty-one states, identifies U.S. presidents with hooks for hands, describes the menu items in addition to eel at the first Thanksgiving, and more. Reprint.',9781594482229,'[\'Humor\']',3.5,32,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=QOi9DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(3403,'The Complete Calvin and Hobbes','[\'Bill Watterson\']','Andrews McMeel Publishing','2005-09-01','Brings together every Calvin and Hobbes cartoon that has ever appeared in syndication, along with stories and poems from classic collections.',9780740748479,'[\'Comics & Graphic Novels\']',4.5,131,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=wmjG5g4Yx7gC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(3404,'The Calvin and Hobbes Tenth Anniversary Book','[\'Bill Watterson\