y to call his girlfriend, but strange and desperate people keep calling--one of them a denizen of Hell--begging for or demanding his help.',9780810954793,'[\'Young Adult Fiction\']',3.5,4,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=ugy9LjjBHEQC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(3419,'The Duplicate','[\'William Sleator\']','Puffin','1999','Sixteen-year-old David, finding a strange machine that creates replicas of living organisms, duplicates himself and suffers the horrible consequences when the duplicate turns against him.',9780141304311,'[\'Juvenile Fiction\']',3,5,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=k-j4GC8N-a8C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(3420,'Strange Attractors','[\'William Sleator\']','Puffin','1991-03-01','Max finds himself in possession of a time travel device which is eagerly sought by two desperate men, the scientist who invented it and the scientist\'s alter ego from a different timeline.',9780140345827,'[\'Juvenile Fiction\']',3,1,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=DpgIAAAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(3421,'The Boy Who Couldn\'t Die','[\'William Sleator\']','Harry N. Abrams','2005-04-01','Ken, the only child of rich, indulgent parents, finds a woman who makes him invulnerable to pain and death, but the curse makes him kill while he is dreaming. Reprint.',9780810987906,'[\'Young Adult Fiction\']',4,13,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=72pRXx4LCb0C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(3422,'Among the Dolls','[\'William Sleator\']','Macmillan','2006-05-02','Vicky\'s disappointment in the antique dollhouse she receives for her birthday gives way to curiosity as she is literally drawn into the lives of its unusual inhabitants.',9780765352392,'[\'Juvenile Fiction\']',3.5,7,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=jZWi4nNxuEMC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(3423,'Once, Said Darlene','[\'William Sleator\']','