',9780374299194,'[\'Biography & Autobiography\']',2.5,18,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Z2vOAwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(3428,'A Confederacy of Dunces','[\'John Kennedy Toole\']','Penguin Books, Limited (UK)','1998-12-01','Ignatius J. Reilly of New Orleans, --selfish, domineering, deluded, tragic and larger than life-- is a noble crusader against a world of dunces. He is a modern-day Quixote beset by giants of the modern age. In magnificent revolt against the twentieth century, Ignatius propels his monstrous bulk among the flesh posts of the fallen city, documenting life on his Big Chief tablets as he goes, until his maroon-haired mother decrees that Ignatius must work.',9780140282689,'[\'Humorous stories\']',3,48,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=e8bJQgAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(3429,'A Confederacy of Dunces','[\'John Kennedy Toole\']','Penguin Modern Classics','2000','Ignatius Reilly, the hero, is a grotesque Gargantua, in violent revolt against the entire 20th century and what he takes to be the manifold excesses and perversions of the past 400 years. He lumbers through New Orleans leaving chaos in his wake.',9780141182865,'[\'Classical fiction\']',3,49,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=tv77QQAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(3430,'Four Stupid Cupids','[\'Gregory Maguire\']','Harper Collins','2001-12-04','The students\' scheme to find a love match for their beloved teacher on Valentine\'s Day turns into a comedy of errors when four stupid cupids from Ancient Greece try to help.',9780064410724,'[\'Juvenile Fiction\']',3,2,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=471OUKKACq8C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(3431,'Wicked','[\'David Coté\', \'Joan Marcus\', \'Stephen Schwartz\']','Hyperion Books','2005-10-26','So much happened before Dorothy dropped in. Two girls quite accidentally crossed paths: one, pretty and popular; the other smart and ... green. The story of how these two unlikely friends became Glinda the Good and the Wicked Witch of the West has made for the most spellbinding new musical in years: Wicked.',9781401308209,'[\'Music\']',4.5,25,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=GOIHAQAAMAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(3432,'A Little Bit Wicked','[\'Victoria Alexander\']','Harper Collins','2009-10-13','Who will be the last unmarried man standing? No man in his right mind would want to get married, but every duke, earl, and viscount knows that a fellow must do his duty in the end. So four of London\'s most desirable gentlemen make a wager—the prize going to the one who remains unwed the longest. Gideon Pearsall, Viscount Warton, thinks he has a fair shot at winning. After all, he\'s managed to enjoy the favors of many a lady while resisting the parson\'s noose. Even when he\'s stopped dead in his tracks by the most scandalous woman in all of London—Judith, Lady Chester—he vows to have her bedded but never wedded. Beautiful, and more than a little bit naughty, Judith has always kept herself within the bounds of respectability, even while playing by her own rules. And the experience has taught her to avoid marriage. She has no desire to resist Warton\'s hot kisses, and his tempting touch is impossible to ignore. But soon both Judith and Gideon can\'t help but wonder . . . is it possible to be a little bit wicked and still follow your heart?',9780060882624,'[\'Fiction\']',4,6,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=NjhY1H2VIvUC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(3433,'My Wicked, Wicked Ways','[\'Errol Flynn\']','Aurum Press','2005','This book, illustrated for the first time with two dozen photos, reveals an introspective and enigmatic personality previously hidden behind a hedonistic facade.',9781845130497,'[\'Actors and actresses\']',4,6,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=641bPwAACAAJ&printsec=frontcove