ess','2001','In 1870 Bismarck ordered the Prussian Army to invade France, inciting one of the most dramatic conflicts in European history. It transformed not only the states-system of the Continent but the whole climate of European moral and political thought. The overwhelming triumph of German military might, evoking general admiration and imitation, introduced an era of power politics, which was to reach its disastrous climax in 1914. First published in 1961 and now with a new introduction, The Franco-Prussian War is acknowledged as the definitive history of one of the most dramatic and decisive conflicts in the history of Europe.',9780415266710,'[\'Foreign Language Study\']',3,2,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=qNQFngEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(3558,'Hadji Murâad','[\'graf Leo Tolstoy\']','Random House Digital, Inc.','2003','Tells the story of Hadji Murad, a Muslim warrior of the Caucasus, caught between the Russians and the Chechens in 1851-1852.',9780812967111,'[\'Fiction\']',3.5,10,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=OYk-DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(3559,'Shahnameh','[\'Firdawsī\']','Penguin Classics','2007','A new translation of the late-tenth-century Persian epic follows its story of pre-Islamic Iran\'s mythic time of Creation through the seventh-century Arab invasion, tracing ancient Persia\'s incorporation into an expanding Islamic empire. Reprint. 35,000 first printing.',9780143104933,'[\'Poetry\']',4,3,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=HHXZCwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(3560,'Buddhism','[\'Huston Smith\', \'Philip Novak\']','HarperOne','2004-12-14','A concise and up-to-date guide to the history, teachings, and practice of Buddhism by two luminaries in the field of world religions.',9780060730673,'[\'Religion\']',4,3,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=d_XvlgEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(3561,'Beneath the Wheel','[\'Hermann Hesse\']','Macmillan','2003-07','Hans Giebernath, a promising young student from a respectable Black Forest village, feels stiffled by the dull uniformity of the academic system. Reprint.',9780312422301,'[\'Fiction\']',3,5,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=3_djQaQ0BEkC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(3562,'LOVE MODE Volume 5: (Yaoi)','[\'Yuki Shimizu\']','Blu','2007-05-08','Follows couples and characters who visit the Blue Boy, an exclusive male dating club.',9781598160147,'[\'Comics & Graphic Novels\']',4,1,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=HYDIAAAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(3563,'LOVE MODE Volume 2: (Yaoi)','[\'Yuki Shimizu\']','Blu','2006-03-07','Follows couples and characters who visit the Blue Boy, an exclusive male dating club.',9781598160116,'[\'Comics & Graphic Novels\']',4,1,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=BHatAAAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(3564,'The Black Sheep','[\'Honore Balzac\']','ePenguin','2005-09-29','Philippe and Joseph Bridau are two extremely different brothers. The elder, Philippe, is a superficially heroic soldier and adored by their mother Agathe. He is nonetheless a bitter figure, secretly gambling away her savings after a brief but glorious career in Napoleon\'s army. His younger brother Joseph, meanwhile, is fundamentally virtuous - but their mother is blinded to his kindness by her disapproval of his life as an artist. Foolish and prejudiced, Agathe lives on unaware that she is being cynically manipulated by her own favourite child, but will she ever discover which of her sons is truly the black sheep of the family? A dazzling depiction of the power of money and the cruelty of life in nineteenth-century France, The Black Sheep compellingly explores is a compelling exploration of the nature of deceit.',9780140442373,'[\'Fiction\']',3.5,3,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=HdzyzAEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(3565,'A Harlot High and Low','[\'Honore Balzac\']','Penguin Classics','1970','Handsome would-be poet Lucien Chardon is poor and naive, but highly ambitious. Failing to make his name in his dull provincial hometown, he is taken up by a patroness, the captivating married woman Madame de Bargeton, and prepares to forge his way in the glamorous beau monde of Paris. But Lucien has entered a world far more dangerous than he realized, as Madame de Bargeton\'s reputation becomes compromised and the fickle, venomous denizens of the courts and salons conspire to keep him out of their ranks. Lucien eventually learns that, wherever he goes, talent counts for nothing in comparison to money, intrigue and unscrupulousness. Lost Illusions is one of the greatest novels in the rich procession of the Comedie humaine, Balzac\'s panoramic social and moral history of his times.',9780140442328,'[\'Fiction\']',4,4,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=tcVnaPgSagAC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(3566,'Cousin Pons','[\'Honore Balzac\']','ePenguin','2006-06-29','Mild, harmless and ugly to behold, the impoverished Pons is an ageing musician whose brief fame has fallen to nothing. Living a placid Parisian life as a bachelor in a shared apartment with his friend Schmucke, he maintains only two passions: a devotion to fine dining in the company of wealthy but disdainful relatives, and a dedication to the collection of antiques. When these relatives become aware of the true value of his art collection, however, their sneering contempt for the parasitic Pons rapidly falls away as they struggle to obtain a piece of the weakening man\'s inheritance. Taking its place in the Human Comedy as a companion to Cousin Bette, the darkly humorous Cousin Pons is among of the last and greatest of Balzac\'s novels concerning French urban society: a cynical, pessimistic but never despairing consideration of human nature.',9780140442052,'[\'Fiction\']',4,2,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=qVrTzAEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(3567,'Understanding Media','[\'Mcluhan Marshall\', \'Marshall McLuhan\']','Corte Madera, CA : Gingko Press','2003','McLuhan\'s view of a media-sculpted society of the future.',9781584230731,'[\'Political Science\']',4.5,8,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=m7poAAAAIAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(3568,'The Best American Sports Writing 2006','[\'Glenn Stout\', \'Michael Lewis\']','Mariner Books','2006','Includes articles chosen from magazines and newspapers on topics ranging from bullfighting to basketball, baseball, and boxing',9780618470228,'[\'Sports & Recreation\']',4,8,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=4bry8JuAiPEC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(3569,'Pearl S. Buck','[\'Peter Conn\', \'Peter J. Conn\']','Cambridge University Press','1998-01-28','Describes the literary, social, and personal accomplishments of the Nobel- and Pulitzer-prize-winning author and activist.',9780521639897,'[\'Biography & Autobiography\']',4,1,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=fxeiP7INFNcC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(3570,'Bright Lights, Big Ass','[\'Jen Lancaster\']','Penguin','2007','A hilarious new memoir by the best-selling author of Bitter Is the New Black chronicles the not-so-wonderful moments of her life in the big city, from reporting rude neighbors to Homeland Security or harboring a crush on her grocery store clerk, to fighting and losing the Battle of the Stairmaster. Original.',9780451221254,'[\'Biography & Autobiography\']',3.5,43,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=mpSuFnlGo5MC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(3571,'Morrigan\'s Cross','[\'Nora Roberts\']','Penguin','2006','As the powerful vampire Lilith prepares to quench her thirst for destruction by unleashing her fury in battle, a medieval sorcerer, one of the circle of six charged by the goddess Morrigan, must travel through time to stop her.',9780515141658,'[\'Fiction\']',3,69,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=kL_M8m6QXlEC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(3572,'Rebellion','[\'Nora Roberts\']','Silhouette','2006','Despite the enmity between their two countries, Brigham Langston, a handsome English lord, finds himself drawn to the beautiful Serena MacGregor, a hot-tempered Scottish hoyden, in a historical romance that serves as a prequel to Roberts\'s best-selling MacGregor series. Reprint.',9780373285433,'[\'Fiction\']',3.5,5,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=RkGYAAAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(3573,'Dream Makers','[\'Nora Roberts\']','Silhouette','2006','Lion trainer Jo Wilder finds herself falling for Keane Prescott, a lawyer who inherits ownership of the circus; and, Megan Miller finds herself falling for David Katcherton, a sexy stranger who offers to buy her grandfather\'s amusement park.',9780373285242,'[\'Fiction\']',4,6,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=JuSFdVARp5oC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(3574,'Spellbound','[\'Nora Roberts\']','Penguin','2005','This is a novella that previously appeared in Nora Roberts\' anthology, A Little Magic.',9780515140774,'[\'Fiction\']',4,19,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=iYbKRHMrCloC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(3575,'Angels Fall','[\'Nora Roberts\']','Putnam Publishing Group','2006','The sole survivor of a brutal crime, Reece Gilmore seeks refuge from the terror of the past in Angel\'s Fist, Wyoming, only to become an eyewitness to a possible murder, but when all evidence of the crime vanishes, no one seems to believe her, except for Brody, a gruff loner who becomes her only hope of escaping a killer. 750,000 first printing.',9780399153723,'[\'Fiction\']',4,30,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=m9hlAAAAMAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(3576,'Three Complete Novels','[\'Nora Roberts\']','Penguin','2001','Three dramatic tales of romantic suspense journey from a Montana ranch to a Virginia horse farm to an island off the coast of Georgia in an omnibus anthology that features True Betrayals, Montana Sky, and Sanctuary. 20,000 first printing.',9780399147319,'[\'Fiction\']',4.5,2,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=RM4CNsqScQ8C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(3577,'Public Secrets','[\'Nora Roberts\']','Bantam','2006-07','Emma, a celebrity child who grew up amidst painful secrets, struggles to break free from her past, but her newfound love for a caring detective is challenged by repressed memories, murderous secrecy, and seduction. Reprint.',9780553589474,'[\'Fiction\']',4,1,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=S4wRrGr5yqcC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(3578,'Kissing in Manhattan','[\'David Schickler\']','Dial Press','2002','At the Preemption, a mysterious apartment building with a prophetic doorman named Sender, the destinies of an offbeat group of tenants intertwine with the lives of three characters--James Branch, a shy accountant attached to the building\'s antique elevator; Wall Street lothario Patrick Rigg; and Rally McWilliams, an aspiring writer searching for a soulmate, in a collection of interlinked stories. Reissue. 45,000 first printing.',9780385335676,'[\'Fiction\']',2,41,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=YwFc2AvqtAYC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(3579,'Making Democracy Work','[\'Robert D. Putnam\', \'Robert Leonardi\', \'Raffaella Nanetti\']','Greenwood Publishing Group','1993','Why do some democratic governments succeed and others fail? In a world full of hope for democratization but wary of government failure, this book offers empirical evidence for the importance of civic community in developing successful institutions. As part of a unique experiment begun in 1970 when Italy created new governments for each of its regions - regions that vary greatly from the standpoint of wealth, social structure, and political leanings - Robert Putnam and his collaborators spent two decades evaluating the performance of these governments in such fields as agriculture, housing, and health services. Their findings were surprising: regions that enjoy effective government in the 1990s have inherited a legacy of civic engagement that can be traced back to the early Middle Ages. Just as Tocqueville traveled to America to try to understand democracy, Putnam and his colleagues draw broad lessons for democratic theory from their twenty-year journey through Italy. Their conclusions challenge the simple-minded thesis of the primacy of economics and the easy optimism of social engineers. Based on dozens of case studies and thousands of interviews with politicians, community leaders, and ordinary citizens, this book illuminates patterns of associationism, trust, and cooperation that facilitate good governance and economic prosperity. It also contributes to the discussion of democracy in the newly freed lands of Eurasia and the developing world and to the gathering debate about how to revitalize democracy in America.',9780691037387,'[\'Political Science\']',3,1,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=6hpoGGrHH-oC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(3580,'A Random Walk Down Wall Street','[\'Burton Gordon Malkiel\']','W. W. Norton & Company','2003','An updated edition of the investor\'s classic guide includes new chapters showing individuals how to tailor their financial objectives to each stage of life and how to meet the challenges of investing following the dot-com crash.',9780393057829,'[\'Business & Economics\']',4,12,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=0uEcVn0MAu0C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(3581,'Identity Crisis','[\'Brad Meltzer\']','Dc Comics','2006-08-01','The crimefighting community is devastated by the death of one of their own when Sue Dibny, the wife of Elongated Man, is murdered in her home, leading to a search for clues and suspects. Reprint.',9781401204587,'[\'Comics & Graphic Novels\']',3.5,25,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=DnsqAAAAYAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(3582,'Superman','[\'Kurt Busiek\', \'Stuart Immonen\']','Dc Comics','2013','When Clark Kent suddenly finds that he has powers like those of his fictional namesake, he attempts to perform humanitarian superfeats while keeping his identity secret, but government agents discover who he is.',9781401204518,'[\'Comics & Graphic Novels\']',4,7,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=OAn4QwAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(3583,'The Dissociative Identity Disorder Sourcebook','[\'Deborah Haddock\']','McGraw Hill Professional','2001-07-31','Finally, a book that addresses your concerns about DID From Eve to Sybil to Truddi Chase, the media have long chronicled the lives of people with dissociative identity disorder (DID), formerly known as multiple personality disorder. The Dissociative Identity Disorder Sourcebook serves as a much-needed bridge for communication between the dissociative individual and therapists, family, and friends who also have to learn to deal with the effects of this truly astonishing disorder.',9780737303940,'[\'Health & Fitness\']',3,1,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=iZjP9ZsHN6YC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(3584,'Identity','[\'Milan Kundera\']','Harper','1998-04-21','Milan Kundera\'s Identity translated from the French by Linda Asher. There are situations in which we fail for a moment to recognize the person we are with, in which the identity of the other is erased while we simultaneously doubt our own. That also happens with couples -- indeed, above all with couples, because lovers fear more than anything else losing sight of the loved one. With stunning artfulness in expanding and playing variations on the meaningful moment, Milan Kundera has made this situation -- and the vague sense of panic it inspires -- the very fabric of his new novel. Here brevity goes hand in hand with intensity, and a moment of bewilderment marks the start of a labyrinthine journey during which the reader repeatedly crosses the border between the real and the unreal, between what occurs in the world outside and what the mind creates in its solitude. Of all contemporary writers, only Kundera can transform such a hidden and disconcerting perception into the material for a novel, one of his finest, most painful, and most enlightening. Which, surprisingly, turns out to be a love story.',9780060175641,'[\'Fiction\']',3.5,10,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=ESmZQgAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(3585,'Slowness','[\'Milan Kundera\']','Harper Collins','1997-04-11','Milan Kundera\'s lightest novel, a divertimento, an opera buffa, Slowness is also the first of this author\'s fictional works to have been written in French. Disconcerted and enchanted, the reader follows the narrator of Slowness through a midsummer\'s night in which two tales of seduction, separated by more than two hundred years, interweave and oscillate between the sublime and the comic. Underlying this libertine fantasy is a profound meditation on contemporary life: about the secret bond between slowness and memory, about the connection between our era\'s desire to forget and the way we have given ourselves over to the demon of speed. And about dancers possessed by the passion to be seen, for whom life is merely a perpetual show emptied of every intimacy and every joy.',9780060928414,'[\'Fiction\']',3,8,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=czPAd_xrPyMC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(3586,'Learned Optimism','[\'Martin E. P. Seligman\']','Vintage','2006','An authority on cognitive psychology and motivation documents the positive effects of optimism on the quality of life and provides a program of specific exercises designed to break the pessimism habit while developing an optimistic outlook. Reprint. 25,000 first printing.',9781400078394,'[\'Psychology\']',4,12,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=JYxIDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(3587,'Homer Price','[\'Robert McCloskey\']','Puffin','2005-12','Six episodes in the life of Homer Price include one in which he and his pet skunk capture four bandits and another about a donut machine on the rampage. Reissue.',9780142404157,'[\'Juvenile Fiction\']',4,11,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=XVifGAAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(3588,'The Classical World','[\'Robin Lane Fox\']','Basic Books','2005','Armies and empires, statesmen and tyrants--the acclaimed historian Robin Lane Fox vividly recounts the history of two great civilizations and one thousand years that forged the Western world',9780465024964,'[\'History\']',1,1,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Srhcjy8JTaEC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(3589,'The Children\'s Homer','[\'Padraic Colum\']','Simon and Schuster','2004-07','Publishers WeeklyColum\'s stirring telling of the Greek epics is unequaled as an introduction to the classic myths for young readers.',9780689868832,'[\'Juvenile Fiction\']',3.5,4,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=_ySymvznW8oC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(3590,'The Coalwood Way','[\'Homer H. Hickam\']','Island Books','2001','Continuing the story of the Rocket Boys of Coalwood, West Virginia, the author recounts his senior year in high school, while the forces of change bring Coalwood to a difficult crossroads and strain threatens to tear apart the Hickam home.',9780440237167