an Nights is a treasury of memories, in which fascinating people and places are brought to life. The healing powers Africa can have on those who embrace the land as a place of mystery, superstition, danger, and beauty.',9780060954833,'[\'Biography & Autobiography\']',3.5,2,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=L1DIR1sb-Y0C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(3595,'Love and Saint Augustine','[\'Hannah Arendt\', \'Joanna Vecchiarelli Scott\', \'Judith Chelius Stark\']','University of Chicago Press','1996-01','Editors Joanna Vecchiarelli Scott and Judith Chelius Stark make Hannah Arendt\'s important early work accessible for the first time. Here is a completely corrected and revised English translation that incorporates Arendt\'s own substantial revisions and provides additional notes based on letters, contracts, and other documents. A revelation that may force us to reconsider the traditional interpretation of Arendt\'s work.--KIRKUS REVIEWS.',9780226025971,'[\'Family & Relationships\']',4,1,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=YqI3H-TKBGkC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(3596,'Healthy Cooking for IBS','[\'Sophie Braimbridge\', \'Erica Jankovich\']','Stewart, Tabori and Chang','2006-04-01','A noted chef and a dietician join forces to create one hundred delicious recipes specifically tailored to the needs of those suffering from Irritable Bowel Syndrome (IBS), featuring an array of dishes for breakfasts, breads, snacks, appetizers, soups, salads, main courses, and desserts, along with information on the syndrome and nutritional and dietary recommendations. Original.',9781584794943,'[\'Cooking\']',2,1,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=cWLmAAAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(3597,'Spells and Sleeping Bags','[\'Sarah Mlynowski\']','Delacorte Books for Young Readers','2007','Rachel and her younger sister, both witches, spend the summer at Camp Wood Lake, where Rach