[\'Robert Irwin\']','Harry N. Abrams','2002-04-30','The English pilgrim Balian of Norwich comes to medieval Cairo on a spy mission and becomes caught up in a series of bizarre intrigues and erotic adventures. Reprint.',9781585672172,'[\'Fiction\']',4,1,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=N45RPgAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(3648,'Continental Drift','[\'Russell Banks\']','Harper Perennial Modern Classics','2007-03-13','A powerful literary classic from one of contemporary fiction\'s most acclaimed and important writers, Russell Banks\'s Continental Drift is a masterful novel of hope lost and gained, and a gripping, indelible story of fragile lives uprooted and transformed by injustice, disappointment, and the seductions and realities of the American dream.',9780060854942,'[\'Fiction\']',4,12,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=VDRLPwAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(3649,'The Darling','[\'Russell Banks\']','Harper Collins','2005-10-11','Set in Liberia and the United States from 1975 through 1991, The Darling is the story of Hannah Musgrave, a political radical and member of the Weather Underground. Hannah flees America for West Africa, where she and her Liberian husband become friends of the notorious warlord and ex-president, Charles Taylor. Hannah\'s encounter with Taylor ultimately triggers a series of events whose momentum catches Hannah\'s family in its grip and forces her to make a heartrending choice.',9780060957353,'[\'Fiction\']',3.5,15,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=_xi3n9OpOhgC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(3650,'Cloudsplitter','[\'Russell Banks\']','Harper Collins','1999-01-27','A triumph of the imagination and a masterpiece of modern storytelling, Cloudsplitter is narrated by the enigmatic Owen Brown, last surviving son of America\'s most famous and still controversial political terrorist and martyr, John Brown. Deeply researched, brilliantly plotted, and peopled with a cast of unforgettable characters both historical and wholly invented, Cloudsplitter is dazzling in its re-creation of the political and social landscape of our history during the years before the Civil War, when slavery was tearing the country apart. But within this broader scope, Russell Banks has given us a riveting, suspenseful, heartbreaking narrative filled with intimate scenes of domestic life, of violence and action in battle, of romance and familial life and death that make the reader feel in astonishing ways what it is like to be alive in that time.',9780060930868,'[\'Fiction\']',4,18,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=gri4AX2RVSEC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(3651,'The Custom of the Country','[\'Edith Wharton\']','Penguin','2006','Edith Wharton\'s novels of manners seem to grow in stature as time passes. Here she draws a beautiful social climber, Undine Sprague, who is a monster of selfishness and honestly doesn\'t know it. Although the worlds she wants to conquer have vanished, Undine herself is amazingly recognizable. She marries well above herself twice and both times fails to recognize her husbands\' strengths of character or the weakness of her own, and it is they, not she, who pay the price.',9780143039709,'[\'Fiction\']',2,1,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=tnco3UU_F0gC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(3652,'Quicksand','[\'Nella Larsen\']','Courier Corporation','2006-09-15','Hypocrisy and prejudice compel a principled racially mixed teacher to desert a steady job and a socially prominent fiancâe.',9780486451404,'[\'Fiction\']',4,16,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=LDw1AwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(3653,'A Companion to Plato\'s Republic','[\'Nicholas P. White\']','Hackett Publishing','1979','A step by step, passage by passage analysis of the complete Republic. White shows how the