xplanatory marginal notes on each page, an index of unprecedented subtlety, and numerous other useful features. In any list of the Great Books of Western Civilization, The Peloponnesian War stands near the top. This authoritative new edition will ensure that its greatness is appreciated by future generations.',9780684827902,'[\'History\']',4.5,17,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=W4MlAyY9wiUC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(3677,'Six Haunted Hairdos','[\'Gregory Maguire\']','Harper Collins','1999-08-18','The rivalry between the boys and girls in Miss Earth\'s class takes a ghostly turn when the girls transform themselves into the Six Haunted Hairdos, but the whole class will have to cast aside their rivalries to stop a real haunting. Reprint.',9780064407205,'[\'Juvenile Fiction\']',3.5,2,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=K0awa6qw-zIC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(3678,'Dancing in the Flames','[\'Marion Woodman\', \'Elinor Dickson\']','Shambhala Publications','1997','Earthy and immensely powerful, the Black Goddess has been a key force in world history, manifested in images as diverse as the Indian goddess Kali and the Black Madonnas of medieval Europe. But images of her have been conspicuously missing from the Western world for centuries--until now. Here, the authors explain the psychological significance of the divine feminine in the lives of modern women and men. 21 illustrations.',9781570623134,'[\'Psychology\']',3,1,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=_F5APgAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(3679,'The Complete Book of Home, Site and Office Security','[\'Bill Phillips\']','McGraw-Hill Education','2006-08-16','Publisher\'s Note: Products purchased from Third Party sellers are not guaranteed by the publisher for quality, authenticity, or access to any online entitlements included with the product. This is a one-stop resource for securing and protecting homes,businesses, and valuable property. Written without technicaljargon, this guide focuses on choosing, installing, andtroubleshooting security devices and systems and offers insideradvice on starting and running a security consulting business.',9780071467445,'[\'Architecture\']',4,1,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=npL8yAEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(3680,'Pope Joan','[\'Donna Woolfolk Cross\']','Random House Digital, Inc.','1997','Set against the turbulent events of the Dark Ages, a fictional account of the controversial figure of historical record profiles a spirited woman who, disguised as a man, rose to rule Christianity as the only woman ever to become pope. Reader\'s Guide included. Reissue. 25,000 first printing.',9780345416261,'[\'Fiction\']',3.5,59,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=It8SIWmw03cC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(3681,'Pope Joan','[\'Lawrence Durrell\', \'Emmanouēl D. Rhoidēs\']','Peter Owen Publishers','1999-01-01','First published in the 1950s, this modern masterpiece is Lawrence Durrell\'s translation and adaptation of Emmanuel Royidis\'s classic Papissa Joanna--the story of history\'s only female pope. The story\'s source is a ninth-century legend: a girl disguised as a monk makes her way from Greece to Rome, is elevated to the throne of St. Peter, and rules over Christendom for a time as Pope John VIII.',9780720610659,'[\'Literary Criticism\']',3,2,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=vxIDAAAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(3682,'Glass Houses','[\'Rachel Caine\']','Penguin','2006','In Morganville, Texas, a town where evil terrorizes the streets under the cover of darkness, Claire Danvers, who has had enough of her current dorm situation, moves off campus and discovers that the town is run by vampires. Original.',9780451219947,'[\'Juvenile Fiction\']',4,163,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=6nFF7IF9OMkC&printsec=frontcover&img=