ing his journey from his decision to leave a life of ease and power to his attainment of spiritual enlightenment.',9780143034360,'[\'Biography & Autobiography\']',3.5,15,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=aJeRPwAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(3689,'The Battle for God','[\'Karen Armstrong\']','Ballantine Reader\'s Circle','2001','Reveals how the fundamentalist movements in Christianity, Judaism, and Islam were born out of a dread of modernity.',9780345391698,'[\'Religion\']',3.5,9,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=hS2PTTqqeowC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(3690,'Muhammad','[\'Karen Armstrong\']','Harper Collins','1993-09-10','This vivid and detailed biography strips away centuries of distortion and myth and presents a balanced view of the man whose religion continues to dramatically affect the course of history.',9780062508867,'[\'Biography & Autobiography\']',4.5,4,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=_nWu0kWqhAIC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(3691,'The Analects of Confucius','[\'Confucius\', \'Roger T. Ames\', \'Henry Rosemont\']','Classics of Ancient China','1999','Based on the oldest extant version of Confucius\'s most influential text, this translation of the Analects serves as an authentic introduction to Confucian thought.',9780345434074,'[\'Fiction\']',5,1,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=2chvDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(3692,'Hiroshima','[\'John Hersey\']','Vintage','1989','The classic tale of the day the first atom bomb was dropped offers a haunting evocation of the memories of survivors and an appeal to the conscience of humanity',9780679721031,'[\'History\']',4,69,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=1z89O0uIlLwC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(3693,'The Wall','[\'John Hersey\']','Vintage','1988','Combines factual history and fictional details to relate the motives, impulses, and deeds of individuals in the Warsaw ghetto during the Nazi persecution',9780394756967,'[\'Fiction\']',4.5,2,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=r5VBDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(3694,'Silent Spring','[\'Rachel Carson\']','Houghton Mifflin Harcourt','2002','Discusses the reckless annihilation of fish and birds by the use of pesticides and warns of the possible genetic effects on humans.',9780618249060,'[\'Nature\']',4,32,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=HeR1l0V0r54C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(3695,'Under the Sea Wind','[\'Rachel Carson\']','Penguin Group USA','1996','Describes the sea birds and sea creatures that inhabit the Eastern coasts of North America.',9780140253801,'[\'Fiction\']',4.5,2,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=fonrQUrGqxgC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(3696,'Back Bay','[\'William Martin\']','Grand Central Publishing','1992-07-01','Meet the Pratt clas. Driven men. Determined women. Through six turbulent generations, they would pursue a lost Paul Revere treasure. And turn a family secret into an obsession that could destroy them. Here is the novel that launched William Martin\'s astonishing literary career and became an instant bestseller. From the grit and romance of old Boston to exclusive -- and dangerous -- Back Bay today, this sweeping saga paints an unforgettable portrait of a powerful dynasty beset by the forces of history...and a heritage of greed, lust, murder and betrayal.',9780446363167,'[\'Fiction\']',3.5,12,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=C_EeTC915JQC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(3697,'A civil action','[\'Jonathan Harr\']','Vintage','1996-08-27','A young Boston trial lawyer is drawn into a case involving two industrial chemical plants and a cluster of childhood leukemia victims that is to encompass nine difficult years and bring him to