nished political career of Warren G. Harding and his scandal-ridden presidency details the Teapot Dome affair, corruption in the Veterans Bureau and Justice Department, extramarital affair, policy decisions, and other important events that marked the administration of the twenty-ninth president. 25,000 first printing.',9780805069563,'[\'Biography & Autobiography\']',2,1,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=nt2ttLTy6IUC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(4738,'Chester','[\'Syd Hoff\']','Harper Collins','1986-04-18','Chester, a wild horse who wants to be tame, comes to the city looking for a home. ‘Reading for fun: the artist’s sense of pacing makes this book race along.’ —Saturday Review.',9780064440950,'[\'Juvenile Fiction\']',4.5,2,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=DiGFBC7APpYC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(4739,'Grizzwold','[\'Syd Hoff\']','Harper Collins','1984-09-05','Grizzwold the lovable bear is having a tough time finding somewhere to live. He\'s too big for most places, and too clumsy for others. He\'s not even any good as a live bearskin rug! Will Grizzwold ever find a home that\'s just right?',9780064440578,'[\'Juvenile Fiction\']',4,1,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Sy_X4g1pvzcC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(4740,'Captain Cat','[\'Syd Hoff\']','Harper Collins','1994-04-22','A patriotic feline, Captain Cat springs out of bed whenever the bugle sounds and he has more stripes than any of the soldiers. But most of all, this young recruit and his best friend Pete know what it really takes to make the army a home—friendship. ‘Hoff continues his string of hits.’ —BL. ‘Hoff has maintained his deft touch with a title that’s sure to appeal to youngsters.’ —SLJ.',9780064441766,'[\'Juvenile Fiction\']',3,1,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=sHz4sQ3mmjwC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(4741,'Once Upon a 