men and savages in central and western New York at the time of the French and Indian War.',9780940450219,'[\'Fiction\']',5,1,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=w6e6z-c9C0YC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(4855,'The Last of the Mohicans','[\'James Fenimore Cooper\']','Bantam Classics','2005-11-29','Illus. in black-and-white. This action-packed edition of James Fenimore Cooper\'s famous adventure brings the wilds of the American frontier and the drama of the French and Indian War to vivid life.',9780553213294,'[\'Fiction\']',4.5,27,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=JqnnTcDDFwUC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(4856,'A River Runs Through It','[\'Norman Maclean\']','University of Chicago Press','1989-05-15','The narrator and his brother become fascinated with fly fishing and the Big Blackfoot River',9780226500607,'[\'Biography & Autobiography\']',4.5,15,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=otrz-KkRIBEC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(4857,'Empires of the Monsoon','[\'Richard Hall\']','HarperCollins Publishers','1998','Until Vasco da Gama discovered the sea-route to the East in 1497-9 almost nothing was known in the West of the exotic cultures and wealth of the Indian Ocean and its peoples. It is this civilization and its destruction at the hands of the West that Richard Hall recreates in this book. Hall\'s history of the exploration and exploitation by Chinese and Arab travellers, and by the Portuguese, Dutch and British alike is one of brutality, betrayal and colonial ambition.',9780006380832,'[\'Africa, East\']',5,2,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=MuPEQgAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(4858,'Fooled By Randomness','[\'Nassim Taleb\']','Random House Incorporated','2005','Contends that randomness and probability have a large impact on life, claims that people regularly fail to recognize that role, and tells how to differentiate between randomness in general and the financial markets in particular.',9780812975215,'[\'Business & Economics\']',3.5,41,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=4eLKm33WneEC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(4859,'Black Hole','[\'Charles Burns\']','Pantheon','2005','Seattle teenagers of the 1970s are suddenly faced with a devastating, disfiguring, and incurable plague that spreads only through sexual contact.',9780375423802,'[\'Comics & Graphic Novels\']',3.5,54,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=dtuEDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(4860,'9-11 [neuf-onze]','[\'Noam Chomsky\', \'Institute Professor & Professor of Linguistics (Emeritus) Noam Chomsky\']','Seven Stories Press','2001','Presents a series of interviews conducted during the first month following the terrorist attacks of September 11, 2001, that discuss reactions to the attacks in the U.S. and abroad, U.S. foreign policy, and the new war on terrorism.',9781583224892,'[\'Political Science\']',3.5,7,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=E5NoWOUhcpYC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(4861,'Syntactic Structures','[\'Noam Chomsky\']','Walter de Gruyter','2002-01-01','Noam Chomsky\'s first book on syntactic structures is one of the first serious attempts on the part of a linguist to construct within the tradition of scientific theory-construction a comprehensive theory of language which may be understood in the same sense that a chemical, biological theory is understood by experts in those fields. It is not a mere reorganization of the data into a new kind of library catalogue, nor another specualtive philosophy about the nature of man and language, but rather a rigorus explication of our intuitions about our language in terms of an overt axiom system, the theorems derivable from it, explicit results which may be compared with new data and other intuitions, all based plainly on an overt theory of the internal structure of languages; and it may well provide an opportunity for the application of explicity measures of simplicity to decide preference of one form over another form of grammar.',9783110172799,'[\'Language Arts & Disciplines\']',3,2,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=SNeHkMXHcd8C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(4862,'The Curious Sofa','[\'Edward Gorey\']','Houghton Mifflin Harcourt','1997','A satire on erotic literature follows the experiences of Alice as she joins a group of unusual people whose actions are enigmatically implied',9780151003075,'[\'Fiction\']',3.5,8,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=F5TzJLpE_98C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(4863,'Ring','[\'Kōji Suzuki\', \'Robert B. Rohmer\', \'Glynne Walley\']','Vertical Incorporated','2004-01-01','Journalist Kazayuki Asakawa\'s investigation into the sudden deaths of four teenagers from heart failure leads to an isolated cabin containing a videotape warning of death in seven days unless certain, now missing, instructions are not followed.',9781932234411,'[\'Fiction\']',3.5,15,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=DRlhnQEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(4864,'Birthday','[\'Koji Suzuki\', \'Meimu\']','Dark Horse Comics','2004','In 2002, The Ring came to American silver screens and brought a whole new style of horror and suspense to the States. Based on a series of novels by Suzuki Koji, The Ring became a media franchise in Japan with its fascinatingly creepy, yet scientific and otherworldly subject matter. Not to mention its very scary monster, the spirit of a girl whose body was dropped in a well many years past. As you\'ll find reading through Dark Horse\'s series of Ring manga, this story is rich with an undergrowth of science and hatred, of strong will behind the murderous ghost of Sadako. Birthday, the fourth in a series of five Ring manga, is a trilogy of stories, each 