 to find the perfect man, but a blind date with a fellow food lover goes horribly wrong when he is stabbed to death. Reprint.',9780425210383,'[\'Fiction\']',3.5,7,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=e1CoxZhUcTMC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(4970,'A New Leash on Death','[\'Susan Conant\']','Berkley','1994','Holly Winter, a writer and amateur sleuth, and her adopted Alaskan malamute, Rowdy, team up to track down a killer lurking at a dog show. Reissue.',9780425146224,'[\'Fiction\']',4,1,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=aKsHAAAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(4971,'The Deed','[\'Lynsay Sands\']','Dorchester Publishing Company Incorporated','2004','A naïve new bride learns that there is more to a wedding night than just a sound sleep, and more to true love than she’s ever imagined.',9780843948103,'[\'Fiction\']',5,1,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=MVyzor_UGHYC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(4972,'The Chase','[\'Lynsay Sands\']','Dorchester Publishing Company Incorporated','2004','A handsome British knight travels to Scotland eager to fulfill a marriage contract, but finds the feisty temper of his stinning bride to be more than he bargained for.',9780843953244,'[\'Fiction\']',5,2,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=xHwJAAAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(4973,'Love Is Blind','[\'Lynsay Sands\']','Leisure Books','2006','Clumsy Clarissa Crambray has a problem--she can\'t see without her glasses. But when she stumbles onto a scarred yet honorable nobleman, it may be a match made in heaven. Original.',9780843955002,'[\'Fiction\']',4.5,7,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=7s_DAAAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(4974,'Standard Catalog of Smith & Wesson','[\'Jim Supica\', \'Richard Nahas\']','Gun Digest Books','2007-01-03','Smith & Wesson outfitted some of the biggest and boldest gunfighters, both actual and fictional, including Wild Bill Hickock, Buffalo Bill and Dirty Harry, whose exploits are still legendary. Today a renewed Smith & Wesson corporation is back in the front of the pack. Standard Catalog of Smith & Wesson, 3rd Edition combines full color photos with details collectors need to identify and better appreciate all Smith & Wesson firearms. For fans of Smith & Wesson firearms, this book is a must-have. This work provides easy-to-locate listings organized by model ad year of manufacture to quickly and accurately identify firearms. With more than 775 models of Smith & Wesson guns and variations, including many models not found in other firearm-pricing guides, this is the book for any Smith & Wesson gun-toting fan.',9780896892934,'[\'Sports & Recreation\']',5,11,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=fvdouQEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(4975,'Korea\'s Place in the Sun: A Modern History (Updated)','[\'Bruce Cumings\']','W. W. Norton & Company','2005-09-17','A narrative chronicle of modern Korea focuses on the country\'s turbulent twentieth-century history, discussing its 1910 loss of independence, its years under Japanese rule, its division and the Korean War, and its postwar recovery and economic growth.',9780393327021,'[\'History\']',4,8,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=yKN_q-TqYYgC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(4976,'Son of Superman','[\'Howard V. Chaykin\', \'David Tischman\']','Dc Comics','1999','With Superman being assumed dead for fifteen years, Superman\'s son, Jon Kent, suddenly awakens to his extraordinary powers and his real identity, and goes in search of his mother, Lois Lane, and the secret behind his father\'s disappearance.',9781563895951,'[\'Comics & Graphic Novels\']',4,1,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=0rAxNgAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(4977,'The Burglar Who Thought He Was Bogart','[\'Lawrence Block\']','HarperTorch','2006-10-31','Bookseller Bernie Rhodenbarr\'s in love—with an exotic Eastern European beauty who shares his obsession with Humphrey Bogart movies. He\'s in heaven, munching popcorn with his new amour every night at a Bogart Film Festival—until their Casablanca-esque idyll is cut short by his other secret passion: burglary. When he\'s hired to pilfer a portfolio of valuable documents from a Park Avenue apartment, Bernie can hardly refuse. But the occupant\'s early return forces Bernie to flee empty-handed—and he soon finds himself implicated in a murder. Before you can say who stole the strawberries? he\'s hunting for a killer, up to his neck in the outrageous intrigues of a tiny Balkan nation . . . and menaced by more sinister fat men and unsavory toadies than the great Bogie himself butted heads with in pursuit of that darn bird!',9780060872793,'[\'Fiction\']',4,9,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=TaXSmAEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(4978,'Hit Parade','[\'Lawrence Block\']','Harper Collins','2006-07-03','Introspective professional assassin John Keller, the anti-hero of Hit Man and Hit List, continues to ponder his life, the ethics of his lethal career, and his possible retirement as he returns in an all-new mystery adventure. 100,000 first printing.',9780060840884,'[\'Fiction\']',3.5,7,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=KYR8gZgkECoC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(4979,'The Girl with the Long Green Heart','[\'Lawrence Block\']','Hard Crime Case','2005-10-03','Evelyn Stone, the secretary to real-estate entrepreneur Wallace Gunderman and his spurned lover, teams up with Johnny Hayden and Doug Rance to make their scheme to take Gunderman for all he is worth suceed. Reprint.',9780843955859,'[\'Fiction\']',4,10,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Gsfd8ZLpaH8C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(4980,'Writing the Novel from Plot to Print','[\'Lawrence Block\']','Writers Digest Books','1985','Block covers every step of the novel writing and selling process to help writers deliver a salable manuscript to the right editor\'s desk.',9780898792089,'[\'Reference\']',3,1,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Y9suepLKnekC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(4981,'Boeing Versus Airbus','[\'John Newhouse\']','Knopf','2007','Chronicles the high-stakes rivalry between the world\'s two largest aircraft manufacturers--companies that will bet the house on a single airplane. Long one of America\'s most successful corporations--and its biggest exporter--Boeing struggled to maintain5',9781400043361,'[\'Business & Economics\']',4,1,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=oR8lKWAfsFEC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(4982,'Fabulous Small Jews','[\'Joseph Epstein\']','Mariner Books','2004','A collection of eighteen stories featuring a host of characters at various crossroads and turning points in their lives, covering such themes as identity, family love, and repressed impulses.',9780618446582,'[\'Fiction\']',4,1,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=sVC2mAEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(4983,'Feast','[\'Nigella Lawson\']','Hyperion','2004-10-27','Nigella Lawson, Gourmet magazine\'s It Girl, New York Times Dining In columnist, and bestselling cookbook author, is celebrating life -- and you\'re invited. Feast, Nigella\'s most festive book yet, offers savory, spicy, and delicious recipes for Thanksgiving, Christmas, Hanukah, Eid, New Year\'s, Passover, Easter gatherings, and any time you want to celebrate food and life. This book is filled with festive recipes, and in it, Nigella offers tips, tricks, and shortcuts that will ensure you dine with ease, style, and fun. Feast also includes some surprising gems, like Nigella\'s Chocolate Cake Hall of Fame, and her best cheeseburger. And like her other cookbooks, Feast is a cookbook that will be treasured all yea