r tiles.',9781400080465,'[\'Biography & Autobiography\']',3,29,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=dSdeseR-QKYC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(5006,'The OK Book','[\'Amy Krouse Rosenthal\']','HarperCollins','2007-04-24','In this clever and literal play on words, OK is turned on its side, upside down, and right side up to show that being OK can really be quite great. Whether OK personifies an OK skipper, an OK climber, an OK lightning bug catcher, or an OK whatever there is to experience, ok is an OK place to be. And being OK just may lead to the discovery of what makes one great. With spare yet comforting illustrations and text, Amy Krouse Rosenthal and Tom Lichtenheld celebrate the real skills and talents children possess, encouraging and empowering them to discover their own individual strengths and personalities. All ages',9780061152559,'[\'Juvenile Fiction\']',4,11,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=iErkngEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(5007,'Bittersweet','[\'Alice Medrich\']','Artisan Books','2003-01-01','Presents a collection of 125 recipes in which chocolate plays a key role, including such treats as brownies, chocolate cake, ice cream, soufflées, and crepes.',9781579651602,'[\'Cooking\']',4.5,3,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=lxrZcjX4DNwC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(5008,'Cocolat','[\'Alice Medrich\']','Grand Central Publishing','1990-10-01','For the millions of chocolate lovers everywhere, here is a stunning dessert cookbook complete with lavish, mouth-watering, full-color photographs, from the respected gourmet known to her peers as Madam Cocolat.',9780446514194,'[\'Cooking\']',5,2,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=gYAsPAAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(5009,'The Bread Baker\'s Apprentice','[\'Peter Reinhart\']','Springer Science & Business','2001','Co-founder of the Brother Juniper\'s Bakery i