om the forces of evil.',9780743296168,'[\'Fiction\']',4,4,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=62tLnSyQLTAC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(5185,'The Prestige','[\'Christopher Priest\']','Macmillan','2006-10-03','In 1878, two young stage magicians clash in a darkened salon during the course of a fraudulent seance, and from this moment they try to expose and outwit each other at every turn.',9780765356178,'[\'Fiction\']',3.5,54,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=yQX2sAWAPOEC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(5186,'The Handmaid\'s Tale','[\'Margaret Atwood\']','Malofilm Video','2006','(Book Jacket Status: Jacketed) A gripping vision of our society radically overturned by a theocratic revolution, Margaret Atwood’s The Handmaid\'s Tale has become one of the most powerful and most widely read novels of our time. Offred is a Handmaid in the Republic of Gilead, serving in the household of the enigmatic Commander and his bitter wife. She may go out once a day to markets whose signs are now pictures because women are not allowed to read. She must pray that the Commander makes her pregnant, for in a time of declining birthrates her value lies in her fertility, and failure means exile to the dangerously polluted Colonies. Offred can remember a time when she lived with her husband and daughter and had a job, before she lost even her own name. Now she navigates the intimate secrets of those who control her every move, risking her life in breaking the rules. Like Aldous Huxley’s Brave New World and George Orwell’s Nineteen Eighty-Four, The Handmaid\'s Tale has endured not only as a literary landmark but as a warning of a possible future that is still chillingly relevant.',9780771008740,'[\'Dystopias\']',4,498,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=9orUvwEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(5187,'The BFG','[\'Roald Dahl\', \'David Wood\', \'Jane Walmsley\']','Puffin','2007-02-01','With notes on staging, props, and costumes, a collection of plays based on the author\'s book can be performed with the minimum of experience or resources. Reprint.',9780142407929,'[\'Juvenile Nonfiction\']',5,1,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=aDf-OwAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(5188,'Hard Drive','[\'James Wallace\', \'Jim Erickson\']','Harper Collins','1993-06-01','Chronicles the career of Chairman Bill Gates, the computer whiz kid who commands the powerful Microsoft computer software empire.',9780887306297,'[\'Business & Economics\']',5,1,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=XdYOGBhp0SAC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(5189,'Bill Gates','[\'Sara Barton-Wood\']','Heinemann/Raintree','2001','Presents the life of Bill Gates, from his childhood, to his education, and to his days as mastermind and head of Microsoft a multi-billion dollar computer software company.',9780739844328,'[\'Juvenile Nonfiction\']',3,1,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=MVyuAoFNFRMC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(5190,'Make Four Million Dollars by Next Thursday!','[\'Stephen Manes\']','Yearling Books','1996','Jason attracts a lot of attention when he starts following the zany advice in a get-rich-quick book by the bizarre Dr. Silverfish.',9780440413707,'[\'Juvenile Fiction\']',4,1,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=uBbkVH1kFQ8C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(5191,'Masters of Enterprise','[\'H.W. Brands\']','Free Press','1999-06-07','Tells the stories of individuals who created great wealth by seizing opportunities that no one else saw',9780684854731,'[\'Business & Economics\']',4,2,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=aN6FAAAAIAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(5192,'The Devil in the Junior League','[\'Linda Francis Lee\']','Macmillan','2006-08-22','A member of the exclusive Junior League of Willow Creek, Texas, Fre