oogle.com/books/content?id=6QOXQgAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(5416,'Desolation Jones','[\'Warren Ellis\', \'J. H. Williams\', \'José Villarrubia\']','Wildstorm','2006','A former field agent for M16, Michael Jones was the first surviving victim of the Desolation Test, a radically dangerous procedure cooked up by the British government. Jones was intravenously kept alive while being force-fed a steady diet of horrific data and images non-stop as stimulants were continuously pumped into his body--keeping him conscious and alert for a solid year. Now retired from the agency, Jones lives in Los Angeles, acting as a private investigator to the secret underground community of ex-spooks who have come in from the cold, and who have no one else to turn to.',9781401211509,'[\'Comics & Graphic Novels\']',4.5,3,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=x2ogAAAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(5417,'Azumanga Daioh','[\'Kiyohiko Azuma\']','Adv Manga','2004','Explores the comedic lives and adventures of a group of high school friends and their teachers in Tokyo.',9781413900309,'[\'Juvenile Fiction\']',4,9,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=E2hQAAAAMAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(5418,'The Queen of the Damned','[\'Anne Rice\']','Ballantine Books','1997-10','Intertwines the stories of rock star and vampire Lestat, beautiful twins haunted by a gruesome tragedy, and Akasha, mother of all vampires, who dreams of godhood.',9780345419620,'[\'Fiction\']',3.5,45,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=y8hvDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(5419,'Exit to Eden','[\'Anne Rampling\', \'Anne Rice\']','Severn House Publishers','1998-05','Welcome to the Club; it\'s there to satisfy your deepest desires - if you can afford to indulge them. Mysterious, elegant, sparkling in the Caribbean sun, the lights never go out, the champagne never stops flowing and the rich and beautiful play tantalising games of pain and pleasure.',9780727853417,'[\'Photographers\']',3,20,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=NeI8PgAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(5420,'El Mesías','[\'Anne Rice\']','EDB FICCION','2006','A novel about the childhood of Christ the Lord based on the Gospels and on the most respected New Testament scholarship.',9788466630030,'[\'Fiction\']',4,4,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=_sL1b7tPKQAC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(5421,'Vittorio, the Vampire','[\'Anne Rice\']','Alfred a Knopf Incorporated','1999','Brought up in Renaissance Florence, Vittorio finds his world shattered when his entire family is destroyed in an act of unholy violence and embarks on a desperate quest for revenge, tormented by his love for the mysterious Vampire Ursula and confronted by demonic enemies. 500,000 first printing. $500,000 ad/promo.',9780375401602,'[\'Fiction\']',3,29,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=b7JkIENr1r4C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(5422,'The Feast of All Saints','[\'Anne Rice\']','Random House','1997','In the days before the Civil War in the old French Quarter of New Orleans there lived the gens de couleur libre, the Free People of Color, a fierce and proud people, descended from slaves and their French and Spanish owners, neither black nor white, but caught between the two - free and yet not free. Among them is Marcel, the mesmeric copper- skinned youth, mercurial, attractive, wild- an artist in the making, he dreams of Paris, and the lure of a brand new art, Daguerrotype. His gentle sister Marie longs for love and marriage in a world ready to sell her charms to the highest bidder. And there is Anna Bella, the beautiful young courtesan; and Dolly Rose, the splendid madame; and Christophe, the brilliant young teacher who has returned from Paris with dangerous ideas.',9780099269472,'[\'African Americans\']',3.5,15,'http