nd small group DVD editions.',9780310257868,'[\'Religion\']',4.5,2,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=m4GxAYrSmyMC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(5489,'Great Russian Short Stories','[\'Paul Negri\']','Courier Corporation','2003-07-29','A collection of twelve Russian short stories including The Queen of Spades, The Overcoat, White Nights, The Signal, and The Lady with the Toy Dog.',9780486429922,'[\'Fiction\']',4.5,2,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=3_CW0gsgDvsC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(5490,'The Portable Dorothy Parker','[\'Dorothy Parker\']','Penguin Classics','2006','Collects short fiction, poems, reviews, and letters from the author renowned for her wit and satiric acumen.',9780143039532,'[\'Literary Collections\']',4,18,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=3xxmAAAAMAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(5491,'The Collected Dorothy Parker','[\'Dorothy Parker\']','Penguin Modern Classics','2001','With a biting wit and perceptive insight, Dorothy Parker examines the social mores of her day and exposes the darkness beneath the dazzle. -- Provided by publisher.',9780141182582,'[\'Classical fiction\']',4,1,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=9ch-AAAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(5492,'The Killer Angels','[\'Michael Shaara\']','Random House Digital, Inc.','2004-11-01','In an effort to draw out the Union Army of the Potomac, the Confederate Army invades the North, and the armies clash in a bloody battle at Gettysburg, Pennsylvania, for four days.',9780679643241,'[\'Fiction\']',4,120,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=U72awDmOvxcC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(5493,'The Best American Travel Writing 2006','[\'Tim Cahill\', \'Jason Wilson\']','Mariner Books','2006','Presents an anthology of the best travel writing published in the previous year, selected from magazines, newspapers, and web sites.',9780618582150,'[\'Travel\']',4,16,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=H8GRNgAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(5494,'The Best American Crime Writing 2006','[\'Mark Bowden\', \'Otto Penzler\', \'Thomas H. Cook\']','Harper Perennial','2006-09-05','A sterling collection of the year\'s most shocking, compelling, and gripping writing about real-life crime, the 2006 edition of The Best American Crime Writing offers fascinating vicarious journeys into a world of felons and their felonious acts. This thrilling compendium includes: Jeffrey Toobin\'s eye-opening exposé in The New Yorker about a famous prosecutor who may have put the wrong man on death row Skip Hollandsworth\'s amazing but true tale of an old cowboy bank robber who turned out to be a classic good-hearted Texas woman Jimmy Breslin\'s stellar piece about the end of the Mob as we know it',9780060815523,'[\'True Crime\']',5,2,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Ec5HlwEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(5495,'How Democratic is the American Constitution?','[\'Robert A. Dahl\']','Yale University Press','2003','The author argues that certain aspects of the American Constitution are deeply flawed and detract from a purely democratic society and includes discussions on the electoral college, the Federalist Papers, and proportional representation.',9780300095241,'[\'History\']',5,2,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=k0jCO_FMbFYC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','en'),(5496,'The Roald Dahl Omnibus','[\'Roald Dahl\']','Hippocrene Books','1987-06','From cover: Perfect bedtime stories for sleepless nights.',9780880291231,'[\'England\']',4,2,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Q3pCFbvW0fUC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','en'),(5497,'Kiss Kiss','[\'Roald Dahl\']','Penguin UK','1962','Eleven Devious, Shocking Stories from the Master of the Unpredictable. What could go wrong when a wife 